404 public void addSymmetricSetOfVertices(SymmetricSet symSet)
405 throws DENOPTIMException
406 {
407 for (SymmetricSet oldSS : symVertices)
408 {
409 for (Integer vid : symSet.getList())
410 {
411 if (oldSS.contains(vid))
412 {
413 throw new DENOPTIMException("Adding " + symSet + " while "
414 + "there is already " + oldSS
415 + " that contains " + vid);
416 }
417 }
418 }
419 symVertices.add(symSet);

486 public Vertex getSourceVertex()
487 {
488 switch (gVertices.size())
489 {
490 case 0:
491 return null;
492 case 1:
493 return getVertexAtPosition(0);
494 }
495 Vertex v0 = getVertexAtPosition(0);
496 for (Edge e : this.getEdgeList())
497 {
498 if (e.getTrgAP().getOwner() == v0)
499 {
500 ArrayList<Vertex> parentTree = new ArrayList<>();
501 getParentTree(v0,parentTree);
502 return parentTree.get(parentTree.size()-1);
503 }
504 }
505 return v0;
506 }

565
572 public ArrayList<Ring> getRingsInvolvingVertex(Vertex[] vs)
573 {
574 ArrayList<Ring> rings = new ArrayList<Ring>();
575 for (Ring r : gRings)
576 {
577 boolean matchesAll = true;
578 for (int i=0; i<vs.length; i++)
579 {
580 if (!r.contains(vs[i]))
581 {
582 matchesAll = false;
583 break;
584 }
585 }
586 if (matchesAll)
587 {
588 rings.add(r);
589 }
590 }
591 return rings;
592 }

631 public boolean hasOrEmbedsRings()
632 {
633 if (gRings.size() > 0)
634 return true;
635 for (Vertex v : gVertices)
636 {
637 if (!(v instanceof Template))
638 continue;
639
640 Template t = (Template) v;
641 if (t.getInnerGraph().hasOrEmbedsRings())
642 return true;
643 }
644 return false;
645 }

772 public void addRing(Vertex vI, Vertex vJ)
773 throws DENOPTIMException
774 {
775 BondType bndTypI = vI.getEdgeToParent().getBondType();
776 BondType bndTypJ = vJ.getEdgeToParent().getBondType();
777 if (bndTypI != bndTypJ)
778 {
779 String s = "Attempt to close rings is not compatible "
780 + "to the different bond type specified by the "
781 + "head and tail APs: (" + bndTypI + "!="
782 + bndTypJ + " for vertices " + vI + " "
783 + vJ + ")";
784 throw new DENOPTIMException(s);
785 }
786 addRing(vI,vJ,bndTypI);
787 jGraph = null;
788 jGraphKernel = null;
789 }

800 public void addRing(Vertex vI, Vertex vJ, BondType bndTyp)
801 {
802 PathSubGraph path = new PathSubGraph(vI,vJ,this);
803 ArrayList<Vertex> arrLst = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
804 arrLst.addAll(path.getVertecesPath());
805 Ring ring = new Ring(arrLst);
806 ring.setBondType(bndTyp);
807 this.addRing(ring);
808 jGraph = null;
809 jGraphKernel = null;
810 }

844 public void removeVertex(Vertex vertex)
845 {
846 if (!gVertices.contains(vertex))
847 {
848 return;
849 }
850
851 vertex.resetGraphOwner();
852 int vid = vertex.getVertexId();
853
854 // delete also any ring involving the removed vertex
855 if (isVertexInRing(vertex))
856 {
857 ArrayList<Ring> rToRm = getRingsInvolvingVertex(vertex);
858 for (Ring r : rToRm)
859 {
860 removeRing(r);
861 }
862 }
863
864 // remove edges involving the removed vertex
865 ArrayList<Edge> eToDel = new ArrayList<>();
866 for (int i=0; i<gEdges.size(); i++)
867 {
868 Edge edge = gEdges.get(i);
869 if (vid == edge.getTrgVertex())
870 {
871 eToDel.add(edge);
872 }
873 // NB: the following allows to break the spanning tree
874 if (vid == edge.getSrcVertex())
875 {
876 eToDel.add(edge);
877 }
878 }
879 for (Edge e : eToDel)
880 {
881 this.removeEdge(e);
882 }
883
884 //delete the removed vertex from symmetric sets, but leave other vertices
885 ArrayList<SymmetricSet> ssToRemove = new ArrayList<SymmetricSet>();
886 for (SymmetricSet ss : symVertices)
887 {
888 if (ss.contains(vid))
889 {
890 if (ss.size() < 3)
891 {
892 ssToRemove.add(ss);
893 }
894 else
895 {
896 // NB: casting needed to remove the object Integer 'vid'
897 // from the list instead of entry number 'vid'
898 ss.remove((Integer) vid);
899 }
900 }
901 }
902 symVertices.removeAll(ssToRemove);
903
904 // remove the vertex from the graph
905 gVertices.remove(vertex);
906
907 jGraph = null;
908 jGraphKernel = null;
909 }

922 public boolean removeVertexAndWeld(Vertex vertex,
923 FragmentSpace fragSpace) throws DENOPTIMException
924 {
925 if (!gVertices.contains(vertex))
926 {
927 return false;
928 }
929
930 ArrayList<Vertex> symSites = getSymVerticesForVertex(vertex);
931 if (symSites.size() == 0)
932 {
933 symSites.add(vertex);
934 } else {
935 //TODO-V3 flip coin to decide if this should be a symmetric operation or not
936 }
937 for (Vertex oldLink : symSites)
938 {
939 GraphUtils.ensureVertexIDConsistency(this.getMaxVertexId());
940 if (!removeSingleVertexAndWeld(oldLink, fragSpace))
941 {
942 return false;
943 }
944 }
945 // Reject deletions that cause the collapse of a 3-atom ring into a
946 // loop (i.e., 1-atom ring) or multiple connection (i.e., a 3-atom ring)
947 for (Ring r : gRings)
948 {
949 // 3 = 1 actual vertex + 2 RCVs
950 if (r.getSize()!=3)
951 continue;
952
953 AttachmentPoint apH = r.getHeadVertex().getEdgeToParent()
954 .getSrcAPThroughout();
955 AttachmentPoint apT = r.getTailVertex().getEdgeToParent()
956 .getSrcAPThroughout();
957
958 if (apH.hasSameSrcAtom(apT) || apH.hasConnectedSrcAtom(apT))
959 return false;
960 }
961 return true;
962 }
963
964//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
965
974 public boolean removeSingleVertexAndWeld(Vertex vertex,
975 FragmentSpace fragSpace) throws DENOPTIMException
976 {
977 if (!gVertices.contains(vertex))
978 {
979 return false;
980 }
981 if (vertex == getSourceVertex())
982 {
983 // Make sure there is something to weld, or give up. This to avoid
984 // trying to remove the scaffold vertex (i.e., a vertex that has no
985 // parents in this graph and the APs of which are only user as
986 // source APs)
987 boolean foundLinkToParent = false;
988 for (AttachmentPoint ap : vertex.getAttachmentPoints())
989 {
990 if (ap.isAvailable() && !ap.isAvailableThroughout())
991 {
992 if (!ap.isSrcInUserThroughout())
993 foundLinkToParent = true;
994 }
995 }
996 if (!foundLinkToParent)
997 return false;
998
999 // When we try to remove the only vertex inside a template, we
1000 // are removing the template itself
1001 if (gVertices.size()==1 && templateJacket!=null)
1002 {
1003 return templateJacket.getGraphOwner().removeSingleVertexAndWeld(
1004 templateJacket, fragSpace);
1005 }
1006 }
1007
1008 // Get all APs that we'll try to weld into the parent
1009 ArrayList<AttachmentPoint> needyAPsOnChildren =
1010 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1011 // And all APs where we could weld onto
1012 ArrayList<AttachmentPoint> freeAPsOnParent =
1013 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1014 // vertex.getAPsFromChilddren(); //No, because it enter templates
1015 Map<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apOnOldToNeedyAP =
1016 new HashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>();
1017 for (AttachmentPoint apOnOld : vertex.getAttachmentPoints())
1018 {
1019 if (!apOnOld.isAvailableThroughout())
1020 {
1021 if (apOnOld.isSrcInUserThroughout())
1022 {
1023 // Links that depart from vertex
1024 AttachmentPoint needyAP =
1025 apOnOld.getLinkedAPThroughout();
1026 // NB: here do not use getSrcThroughout because it would
1027 // enter trg templates rather than staying on their surface.
1028 needyAPsOnChildren.add(needyAP);
1029 apOnOldToNeedyAP.put(apOnOld, needyAP);
1030 } else {
1031 AttachmentPoint apOnParent =
1032 apOnOld.getLinkedAPThroughout();
1033 // NB: here do not use getSrcThroughout because it would
1034 // enter src templates rather than staying on their surface.
1035 freeAPsOnParent.add(apOnParent);
1036 freeAPsOnParent.addAll(apOnParent.getOwner()
1037 .getFreeAPThroughout());
1038 }
1039 }
1040 }
1041
1042 // Get all possible parentAPs-childAPs mappings
1043 List<APMapping> mappings = fragSpace.mapAPClassCompatibilities(
1044 freeAPsOnParent, needyAPsOnChildren, 500);
1045 if (mappings.size() == 0)
1046 {
1047 // No APClass-compatible possibility of removing the link.
1048 return false;
1049 }
1050
1051 // Score mapping to prioritise those that preserve rings.
1052 // This to differentiate from the combination of DELETE+EXTEND operation
1053 // which cannot preserve rings.
1054 List<Integer> preferences = new ArrayList<Integer>();
1055 // Score rings in this level's graph
1056 for (int i=0; i<needyAPsOnChildren.size(); i++)
1057 {
1058 AttachmentPoint needyAP = needyAPsOnChildren.get(i);
1059 preferences.add(0);
1060
1061 Vertex ownerOfNeedy = needyAP.getOwner();
1062 for (Ring r : ownerOfNeedy.getGraphOwner()
1063 .getRingsInvolvingVertex(ownerOfNeedy))
1064 {
1065 // NB: here we stay at the level of the graph owning ownerOfNeedy
1066 Vertex lastBeforeOwnerOfNeedy =
1067 needyAP.getLinkedAP().getOwner();
1068 if (r.contains(lastBeforeOwnerOfNeedy))
1069 {
1070 preferences.set(i, preferences.get(i) + 1);
1071 }
1072 }
1073 }
1074
1075 // Choose best scoring mapping
1076 int maxScore = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
1077 APMapping bestScoringMapping = null;
1078 for (APMapping apm : mappings)
1079 {
1080 int score = 0;
1081 for (AttachmentPoint ap : apm.values())
1082 {
1083 score = score + preferences.get(needyAPsOnChildren.indexOf(ap));
1084 }
1085 if (score > maxScore)
1086 {
1087 maxScore = score;
1088 bestScoringMapping = apm;
1089 }
1090 }
1091
1092 APMapping bestScoringMappingReverse = new APMapping();
1093 for (Entry<AttachmentPoint, AttachmentPoint> e :
1094 bestScoringMapping.entrySet())
1095 {
1096 bestScoringMappingReverse.put(e.getValue(), e.getKey());
1097 }
1098
1099 // Update rings involving vertex directly (i.e., in this graph)
1100 ArrayList<Ring> rToEdit = getRingsInvolvingVertex(vertex);
1101 ArrayList<Ring> ringsToRemove = new ArrayList<Ring>();
1102 for (Ring r : rToEdit)
1103 {
1104 r.removeVertex(vertex);
1105 if (r.getSize() < 3)
1106 ringsToRemove.add(r);
1107 }
1108 for (Ring r : ringsToRemove)
1109 {
1110 removeRing(r);
1111 }
1112
1113 // Remove edges to/from old vertex, while keeping track of edits to do
1114 // in a hypothetical jacket template (if such template exists)
1115 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> newInReplaceOldInInTmpl =
1116 new LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>();
1117 List<AttachmentPoint> oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl =
1118 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1119 for (AttachmentPoint oldAP : vertex.getAttachmentPoints())
1120 {
1121 if (oldAP.isAvailable())
1122 {
1123 // NB: if this graph is embedded in a template, free/available
1124 // APs at this level (and sources at the vertex we are removing)
1125 // are mapped on the jacket templates' surface, and must be
1126 // removed.
1127 if (templateJacket!=null)
1128 {
1129 if (!oldAP.isAvailableThroughout())
1130 {
1131 AttachmentPoint lAP =
1132 oldAP.getLinkedAPThroughout();
1133 if (bestScoringMapping.keySet().contains(lAP))
1134 {
1135 newInReplaceOldInInTmpl.put(
1136 bestScoringMapping.get(lAP), oldAP);
1137 } else if (bestScoringMapping.values().contains(lAP))
1138 {
1139 newInReplaceOldInInTmpl.put(
1140 bestScoringMappingReverse.get(lAP), oldAP);
1141 } else {
1142 oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl.add(oldAP);
1143 }
1144 } else {
1145 oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl.add(oldAP);
1146 }
1147 }
1148 } else {
1149 removeEdge(oldAP.getEdgeUser());
1150 }
1151 }
1152
1153 // Update pointers in symmetric sets in this graph level
1154 // NB: this deals only with the symmetric relations of the removed vertex
1155 // The symm. relations of other removed child vertices are dealt with
1156 // when removing those vertices.
1157 int oldVrtxId = vertex.getVertexId();
1158 ArrayList<SymmetricSet> ssToRemove = new ArrayList<SymmetricSet>();
1159 Iterator<SymmetricSet> ssIter = getSymSetsIterator();
1160 while (ssIter.hasNext())
1161 {
1162 SymmetricSet ss = ssIter.next();
1163 if (ss.contains(oldVrtxId))
1164 {
1165 ss.remove((Integer) oldVrtxId);
1166 }
1167 if (ss.size() < 2)
1168 ssToRemove.add(ss);
1169 }
1170 symVertices.removeAll(ssToRemove);
1171
1172 // Remove the vertex
1173 getVertexList().remove(vertex);
1174 vertex.resetGraphOwner();
1175
1176 // Add new edges (within the graph owning the removed vertex)
1177 List<AttachmentPoint> reconnettedApsOnChilds =
1178 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1179 for (Entry<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> e :
1180 bestScoringMapping.entrySet())
1181 {
1182 AttachmentPoint apOnParent = e.getKey();
1183 AttachmentPoint apOnChild = e.getValue();
1184 if (containsVertex(apOnChild.getOwner())
1185 && containsVertex(apOnParent.getOwner()))
1186 {
1187 Edge edge = new Edge(apOnParent,apOnChild,
1188 apOnParent.getAPClass().getBondType());
1189 addEdge(edge);
1190 reconnettedApsOnChilds.add(apOnChild);
1191 } else {
1192 if (templateJacket!=null)
1193 {
1194 if (containsVertex(apOnParent.getOwner()))
1195 {
1196 templateJacket.updateInnerApID(
1197 newInReplaceOldInInTmpl.get(apOnParent), //AP on old vertex
1198 apOnParent);
1199 reconnettedApsOnChilds.add(apOnChild);
1200 }
1201 if (containsVertex(apOnChild.getOwner()))
1202 {
1203 templateJacket.updateInnerApID(
1204 newInReplaceOldInInTmpl.get(apOnChild), //AP on old vertex
1205 apOnChild);
1206 reconnettedApsOnChilds.add(apOnChild);
1207 }
1208 // The case where neither is contained in 'this' cannot
1209 // occur because of the initial checks that identify
1210 // attempts to remove the only vertex inside a template.
1211 } else {
1212 DENOPTIMException de = new DENOPTIMException("AP '"
1213 + apOnChild + "' seems connected to a template, "
1214 + "no template was found. Possible bug!");
1215 throw de;
1216 }
1217 }
1218 }
1219
1220 // update the mapping of this vertex's APs in the jacket template
1221 if (templateJacket!=null)
1222 {
1223 // Remove all APs that existed only in the old vertex
1224 for (AttachmentPoint apOnOld : oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl)
1225 {
1226 templateJacket.removeProjectionOfInnerAP(apOnOld);
1227 }
1228 }
1229
1230 // Remove branches of child-APs that were not mapped/done
1231 for (AttachmentPoint apOnChild : needyAPsOnChildren)
1232 {
1233 if (!reconnettedApsOnChilds.contains(apOnChild))
1234 {
1235 removeOrphanBranchStartingAt(apOnChild.getOwner());
1236 }
1237 }
1238
1239 jGraph = null;
1240 jGraphKernel = null;
1241
1242 return !this.containsVertex(vertex);
1243 }

1254 public void replaceUnusedRCVsWithCapps(FragmentSpace fragSpace)
1255 throws DENOPTIMException
1256 {
1257 List<Vertex> rcvToReplace = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1258 List<AttachmentPoint> apToCap = new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1259 for (Vertex v : getRCVertices())
1260 {
1261 if (getRingsInvolvingVertex(v).size()==0
1262 && v.getEdgeToParent()!=null)
1263 {
1264 rcvToReplace.add(v);
1265 apToCap.add(v.getEdgeToParent().getSrcAP());
1266 }
1267 }
1268 for (int i=0; i<rcvToReplace.size(); i++)
1269 {
1270 Vertex v = rcvToReplace.get(i);
1271 removeVertex(v);
1272
1273 AttachmentPoint apOnParent = apToCap.get(i);
1274 APClass cappAPClass = fragSpace.getAPClassOfCappingVertex(
1275 apOnParent.getAPClass());
1276
1277 if (cappAPClass != null)
1278 {
1279 Vertex capVrt = fragSpace.getCappingVertexWithAPClass(
1280 cappAPClass);
1281 capVrt.setVertexId(v.getVertexId());
1282 appendVertexOnAP(apOnParent, capVrt.getAP(0));
1283 }
1284 }

1296 protected void reassignSymmetricLabels()
1297 {
1298 //Remove previous labeling
1299 for (Vertex v : gVertices)
1300 v.removeProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID);
1301
1302 Iterator<SymmetricSet> ssIter = getSymSetsIterator();
1303 int i = 0;
1304 while (ssIter.hasNext())
1305 {
1306 SymmetricSet ss = ssIter.next();
1307 String symmLabel = ss.hashCode() + "-" + i;
1308 for (Integer vid : ss.getList())
1309 {
1310 getVertexWithId(vid).setProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID,
1311 symmLabel);
1312 }
1313 i++;
1314 }
1315 for (Vertex v : gVertices)
1316 {
1317 i++;
1318 if (!v.hasProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID))
1319 v.setProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID, v.hashCode()+"-"+i);
1320 }
1321 }

1323//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1324
1329 protected void convertSymmetricLabelsToSymmetricSets()
1330 {
1331 Map<String,List<Vertex>> collectedLabels = new HashMap<>();
1332 for (Vertex v : gVertices)
1333 {
1334 if (v.hasProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID))
1335 {
1336 String label = v.getProperty(
1337 DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID).toString();
1338 if (collectedLabels.containsKey(label))
1339 {
1340 collectedLabels.get(label).add(v);
1341 } else {
1342 List<Vertex> lst = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1343 lst.add(v);
1344 collectedLabels.put(label, lst);
1345 }
1346 v.removeProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.VRTSYMMSETID);
1347 }
1348 }
1349
1350 for (String label : collectedLabels.keySet())
1351 {
1352 List<Vertex> symmvertices = collectedLabels.get(label);
1353
1354 if (symmvertices.size()>1)
1355 {
1356 SymmetricSet ss = null;
1357 for (Vertex v : symmvertices)
1358 {
1359 if (hasSymmetryInvolvingVertex(v))
1360 {
1361 ss = getSymSetForVertex(v);
1362 break;
1363 }
1364 }
1365
1366 if (ss != null)
1367 {
1368 for (Vertex v : symmvertices)
1369 ss.add(v.getVertexId());
1370
1371 } else {
1372 ss = new SymmetricSet();
1373 for (Vertex v : symmvertices)
1374 ss.add(v.getVertexId());
1375 try
1376 {
1377 addSymmetricSetOfVertices(ss);
1378 } catch (DENOPTIMException e)
1379 {
1380 //this can never happen because we are testing for
1381 // preliminary existence of an id in the existing sets.
1382 }
1383 }
1384 }
1385 }
1386 }

1409 public boolean replaceSubGraph(List<Vertex> subGrpVrtxs,
1410 DGraph incomingGraph,
1411 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apMap,
1412 FragmentSpace fragSpace) throws DENOPTIMException
1413 {
1414 for (Vertex vToRemove : subGrpVrtxs)
1415 {
1416 if (!gVertices.contains(vToRemove))
1417 {
1418 return false;
1419 }
1420 }
1421
1422 // Capping groups are removed and, if needed, re-added back
1423 subGrpVrtxs.stream().filter(v -> v.getBuildingBlockType()==BBType.CAP)
1424 .forEach(v -> this.removeVertex(v));
1425 subGrpVrtxs.removeIf(v -> v.getBuildingBlockType()==BBType.CAP);
1426 if (subGrpVrtxs.size() == 0)
1427 {
1428 throw new DENOPTIMException("Capping groups cannot be the only "
1429 + "vertex in a subgraph to replace.");
1430 }
1431
1432 // Refresh the symmetry set labels so that clones of the branch inherit
1433 // the same symmetry set labels.
1434 incomingGraph.reassignSymmetricLabels();
1435
1436 GraphUtils.ensureVertexIDConsistency(this.getMaxVertexId());
1437
1438 // Verify that also the surrounding of vertices in the lists is
1439 // consistent between subGrpVrtxs and verticesToRemove. Even if the
1440 // two are consistent, there can still be differences in the childs.
1441 List<List<Vertex>> compatibleSymSubGrps = new ArrayList<List<Vertex>>();
1442 for (List<Vertex> symmetricSubGrpVrtx : getSymmetricSubGraphs(subGrpVrtxs))
1443 {
1444 boolean skip = false;
1445 for (int iv=0; iv<subGrpVrtxs.size(); iv++)
1446 {
1447 if (skip)
1448 break;
1449 Vertex oriVs = subGrpVrtxs.get(iv);
1450 Vertex symVs = symmetricSubGrpVrtx.get(iv);
1451 List<Vertex> oriVsChildren = oriVs.getChilddren();
1452 List<Vertex> symVsChildren = symVs.getChilddren();
1453
1454 // NB: oriVsChildren does not include CAPs from the
1455 // initial subgraph, while symVsChildren does include the
1456 // corresponding CAPs.
1457 oriVsChildren.removeIf(v -> v.getBuildingBlockType()==BBType.CAP);
1458 symVsChildren.removeIf(v -> v.getBuildingBlockType()==BBType.CAP);
1459 if (oriVsChildren.size()!=symVsChildren.size())
1460 {
1461 // we continue in the outer loop
1462 skip = true;
1463 continue;
1464 }
1465 for (int ic=0; ic<oriVsChildren.size(); ic++)
1466 {
1467 if (skip)
1468 break;
1469 // We have already checked those in the subgraph
1470 if (subGrpVrtxs.contains(oriVsChildren.get(ic)))
1471 continue;
1472 // We do allow the two child to be different vertices, but
1473 // we avoid having one CAP and one not. this because it will
1474 // lead to having free APs on the parent of the first and
1475 // busy APs on the parent of the second. This prevents
1476 // finding a mapping of the free APs.
1477 if (oriVsChildren.get(ic).getBuildingBlockType()
1478 != symVsChildren.get(ic).getBuildingBlockType())
1479 {
1480 skip = true;
1481 continue;
1482 }
1483 }
1484 }
1485 if (!skip)
1486 compatibleSymSubGrps.add(symmetricSubGrpVrtx);
1487 }
1488 if (compatibleSymSubGrps.size()==0)
1489 throw new DENOPTIMException("Failed to detect autosymmetry.");
1490
1491 for (List<Vertex> verticesToRemove : compatibleSymSubGrps)
1492 {
1493 // Prepare incoming graph
1494 DGraph graphToAdd = incomingGraph.clone();
1495 graphToAdd.renumberGraphVertices();
1496 List<Vertex> vertexAddedToThis = new ArrayList<Vertex>(
1497 graphToAdd.gVertices);
1498
1499 // Prepare subgraph (it already does not contain caps)
1500 removeCappingGroupsFromChilds(verticesToRemove);
1501
1502 // Prepare AP mapping projecting the one for subGrpVrtxs
1503 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> localApMap =
1504 new LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>();
1505 for (Map.Entry<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> e : apMap.entrySet())
1506 {
1507 // WARNING! Assumption that subGrpVrtxs and verticesToRemove
1508 // are sorted accordingly to symmetry, which should be the case.
1509 int vrtPosOnOld = subGrpVrtxs.indexOf(e.getKey().getOwner());
1510 int apPosOnOld = e.getKey().getIndexInOwner();
1511 AttachmentPoint apOnOld = verticesToRemove.get(
1512 vrtPosOnOld).getAP(apPosOnOld);
1513
1514 int vrtPosOnNew = incomingGraph.indexOf(e.getValue().getOwner());
1515 int apPosOnNew = e.getValue().getIndexInOwner();
1516 AttachmentPoint apOnNew = graphToAdd.getVertexAtPosition(
1517 vrtPosOnNew).getAP(apPosOnNew);
1518 localApMap.put(apOnOld,apOnNew);
1519 }
1520
1521 if (!replaceSingleSubGraph(verticesToRemove, graphToAdd, localApMap))
1522 {
1523 return false;
1524 }
1525 addCappingGroups(vertexAddedToThis, fragSpace);
1526 }
1527 convertSymmetricLabelsToSymmetricSets();
1528 return true;
1529 }

1531//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1532
1545 public List<List<Vertex>> getSymmetricSubGraphs(
1546 List<Vertex> subGrpVrtxs) throws DENOPTIMException
1547 {
1548 if (subGrpVrtxs.stream().anyMatch(v -> v.getBuildingBlockType()==BBType.CAP))
1549 throw new DENOPTIMException("Capping groups must not be part of "
1550 + "symmetric subgraphs");
1551
1552 List<List<Vertex>> symSites = new ArrayList<List<Vertex>>();
1553
1554 if (subGrpVrtxs.size()==1)
1555 {
1556 for (Vertex sv : getSymVerticesForVertex(subGrpVrtxs.get(0)))
1557 {
1558 ArrayList<Vertex> lst = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1559 lst.add(sv);
1560 symSites.add(lst);
1561 }
1562 if (symSites.size()==0)
1563 {
1564 symSites.add(subGrpVrtxs);
1565 }
1566 return symSites;
1567 }
1568
1569 // Identify the (sole) grand parent.
1570 List<Vertex> thoseWithoutParent = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1571 for (Vertex v : subGrpVrtxs)
1572 {
1573 if (!subGrpVrtxs.contains(v.getParent()))
1574 thoseWithoutParent.add(v);
1575 }
1576 if (thoseWithoutParent.size()!=1)
1577 {
1578 throw new DENOPTIMException("SubGraph has more than one grand "
1579 + "parent.");
1580 }
1581 Vertex sourceOfSubGraph = thoseWithoutParent.get(0);
1582 int numSymmetricSubGraphs = getSymVerticesForVertex(sourceOfSubGraph).size();
1583 if (numSymmetricSubGraphs==0)
1584 {
1585 symSites.add(subGrpVrtxs);
1586 return symSites;
1587 }
1588
1589 // Identify the ends of the subgraph's spanning tree
1590 List<Vertex> thoseWithoutChildren = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1591 for (Vertex v : subGrpVrtxs)
1592 {
1593 if (Collections.disjoint(v.getChilddren(),subGrpVrtxs))
1594 thoseWithoutChildren.add(v);
1595 }
1596
1597 // We want to verify that all the ends of the subgraph's spanning tree
1598 // have the same number of symmetric partners. This, while collecting
1599 // all ends that are outside the subgraph and are symmetric to any of
1600 // the ends belonging to the subgraph. The first, in fact, are the ends
1601 // of the symmetric subgraphs.
1602 Set<Vertex> upperLimits = new HashSet<Vertex>();
1603 Set<Vertex> doneBySymmetry = new HashSet<Vertex>();
1604 for (Vertex upperLimit : thoseWithoutChildren)
1605 {
1606 // We need to understand how many symmetric vertices are already
1607 // within the subgraph
1608 int numInSubGraphReplicas = 1;
1609
1610 if (doneBySymmetry.contains(upperLimit))
1611 continue;
1612
1613 // These are symmetric vertices that do belong to the subgraph
1614 Set<Vertex> symmSitesOnBranch = new HashSet<Vertex>(
1615 getSymVerticesForVertex(upperLimit));
1616 symmSitesOnBranch.retainAll(subGrpVrtxs);
1617 if (symmSitesOnBranch.size()>0)
1618 {
1619 numInSubGraphReplicas = symmSitesOnBranch.size();
1620 doneBySymmetry.addAll(symmSitesOnBranch);
1621 }
1622
1623 List<Vertex> lst = getSymVerticesForVertex(upperLimit);
1624 if (lst.size() != numInSubGraphReplicas*numSymmetricSubGraphs)
1625 {
1626 // The subgraph is not symmetrically reproduced.
1627 symSites.add(subGrpVrtxs);
1628 return symSites;
1629 }
1630 upperLimits.addAll(lst);
1631 }
1632
1633 for (Vertex symSources : getSymVerticesForVertex(sourceOfSubGraph))
1634 {
1635 List<Vertex> symSubGraph = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1636 // The source of the symmetric subgraph is always the first!
1637 symSubGraph.add(symSources);
1638 getChildTreeLimited(symSources, symSubGraph, upperLimits);
1639 //NB: Capping groups are not supposed to be in the list.
1640 symSubGraph.removeIf(v -> v.getBuildingBlockType()==BBType.CAP);
1641 if (symSubGraph.size()!=subGrpVrtxs.size())
1642 {
1643 symSites = new ArrayList<List<Vertex>>();
1644 symSites.add(subGrpVrtxs);
1645 return symSites;
1646 }
1647 symSites.add(symSubGraph);
1648 }
1649
1650 return symSites;
1651 }
1652
1653//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1654
1683 public boolean replaceSingleSubGraph(List<Vertex> subGrpVrtxs,
1684 DGraph newSubGraph,
1685 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apMap)
1686 throws DENOPTIMException
1687 {
1688 if (!gVertices.containsAll(subGrpVrtxs)
1689 || gVertices.contains(newSubGraph.getVertexAtPosition(0)))
1690 {
1691 return false;
1692 }
1693
1694 // Identify vertex that will be added
1695 ArrayList<Vertex> newvertices = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1696 newvertices.addAll(newSubGraph.getVertexList());
1697
1698 // Collect APs from the vertices that will be removed, and that might
1699 // be reflected onto the jacket template or used to make links to the
1700 // rest of the graph.
1701 List<AttachmentPoint> interfaceApsOnOldBranch =
1702 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1703 for (Vertex vToDel : subGrpVrtxs)
1704 {
1705 for (AttachmentPoint ap : vToDel.getAttachmentPoints())
1706 {
1707 if (ap.isAvailable())
1708 {
1709 // being available, this AP might be reflected onto
1710 // jacket template
1711 interfaceApsOnOldBranch.add(ap);
1712 } else {
1713 Vertex user = ap.getLinkedAP().getOwner();
1714 if (!subGrpVrtxs.contains(user))
1715 {
1716 interfaceApsOnOldBranch.add(ap);
1717 }
1718 }
1719 }
1720 }
1721
1722 List<AttachmentPoint> interfaceApsOnNewBranch =
1723 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1724 for (Vertex v : newSubGraph.getVertexList())
1725 {
1726 for (AttachmentPoint ap : v.getAttachmentPoints())
1727 {
1728 if (ap.isAvailable())
1729 {
1730 // being available, this AP will have to be reflected onto
1731 // jacket template
1732 interfaceApsOnNewBranch.add(ap);
1733 }
1734 }
1735 }
1736
1737 // Keep track of the links that will be broken and re-created,
1738 // and also of the relation free APs may have with a possible template
1739 // that embeds this graph.
1740 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>
1741 linksToRecreate = new LinkedHashMap<>();
1742 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,BondType>
1743 linkTypesToRecreate = new LinkedHashMap<>();
1744 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>
1745 inToOutAPForTemplate = new LinkedHashMap<>();
1746 List<AttachmentPoint> oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl = new ArrayList<>();
1747 AttachmentPoint trgAPOnNewLink = null;
1748 for (AttachmentPoint oldAP : interfaceApsOnOldBranch)
1749 {
1750 if (oldAP.isAvailable())
1751 {
1752 // NB: if this graph is embedded in a template, free/available
1753 // APs at this level (and from the old link)
1754 // are mapped on the templates' surface
1755 if (templateJacket!=null)
1756 {
1757 if (oldAP.isAvailableThroughout())
1758 {
1759 if (!apMap.containsKey(oldAP))
1760 {
1761 // An AP of the old link is going to be removed from the
1762 // template-jacket's list of APs
1763 oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl.add(oldAP);
1764 } else {
1765 // This AP is not used, not even outside of the template
1766 // but for some reason the apMapping wants to keep it
1767 inToOutAPForTemplate.put(apMap.get(oldAP),oldAP);
1768 }
1769 } else {
1770 if (!apMap.containsKey(oldAP))
1771 {
1772 throw new DENOPTIMException("Cannot replace subgraph "
1773 + "if a used AP has no mapping.");
1774 } else {
1775 // This AP is not used, not even outside of the template
1776 // but for some reason the apMapping wants to keep it
1777 inToOutAPForTemplate.put(apMap.get(oldAP),oldAP);
1778 }
1779 }
1780 }
1781 continue;
1782 }
1783
1784 if (!apMap.containsKey(oldAP))
1785 {
1786 throw new DENOPTIMException("Cannot replace subgraph if a used "
1787 + "AP has no mapping. Missing mapping for AP "
1788 + oldAP.getIndexInOwner() + " in "
1789 + oldAP.getOwner().getVertexId());
1790 }
1791 AttachmentPoint newAP = apMap.get(oldAP);
1792 linksToRecreate.put(newAP, oldAP.getLinkedAP());
1793 linkTypesToRecreate.put(newAP, oldAP.getEdgeUser().getBondType());
1794
1795 // This is were we identify the edge/ap to the parent of the oldLink
1796 if (!oldAP.isSrcInUser())
1797 {
1798 trgAPOnNewLink = newAP;
1799 }
1800 }
1801
1802 // Identify rings that are affected by the change of vertices
1803 Map<Ring,List<Vertex>> ringsOverSubGraph =
1804 new HashMap<Ring,List<Vertex>>();
1805 for (int iA=0; iA<interfaceApsOnOldBranch.size(); iA++)
1806 {
1807 AttachmentPoint apA = interfaceApsOnOldBranch.get(iA);
1808
1809 if (apA.isAvailable())
1810 continue;
1811
1812 for (int iB=(iA+1); iB<interfaceApsOnOldBranch.size(); iB++)
1813 {
1814 AttachmentPoint apB = interfaceApsOnOldBranch.get(iB);
1815
1816 if (apB.isAvailable())
1817 continue;
1818
1819 Vertex vLinkedOnA = apA.getLinkedAP().getOwner();
1820 Vertex vLinkedOnB = apB.getLinkedAP().getOwner();
1821 for (Ring r : getRingsInvolvingVertex(
1822 new Vertex[] {
1823 apA.getOwner(), vLinkedOnA,
1824 apB.getOwner(), vLinkedOnB}))
1825 {
1826 List<Vertex> vPair = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
1827 vPair.add(r.getCloserToHead(vLinkedOnA, vLinkedOnB));
1828 vPair.add(r.getCloserToTail(vLinkedOnA, vLinkedOnB));
1829 ringsOverSubGraph.put(r, vPair);
1830 }
1831 }
1832 }
1833
1834 // remove the vertex-to-delete from the rings where they participate
1835 for (Ring r : ringsOverSubGraph.keySet())
1836 {
1837 List<Vertex> vPair = ringsOverSubGraph.get(r);
1838 PathSubGraph path = new PathSubGraph(vPair.get(0),vPair.get(1),this);
1839 List<Vertex> verticesInPath = path.getVertecesPath();
1840 for (int i=1; i<(verticesInPath.size()-1); i++)
1841 {
1842 r.removeVertex(verticesInPath.get(i));
1843 }
1844 }
1845
1846 // remove edges with old vertex
1847 for (AttachmentPoint oldAP : interfaceApsOnOldBranch)
1848 {
1849 if (!oldAP.isAvailable())
1850 removeEdge(oldAP.getEdgeUser());
1851 }
1852
1853 // remove the vertex from the graph
1854 for (Vertex vToDel : subGrpVrtxs)
1855 {
1856 // WARNING! This removes rings involving these vertices.
1857 removeVertex(vToDel);
1858 }
1859
1860 // finally introduce the new vertices from incoming graph into this graph
1861 for (Vertex incomingVrtx : newSubGraph.getVertexList())
1862 {
1863 addVertex(incomingVrtx);
1864 }
1865
1866 // import edges from incoming graph
1867 for (Edge incomingEdge : newSubGraph.getEdgeList())
1868 {
1869 addEdge(incomingEdge);
1870 }
1871
1872 // import rings from incoming graph
1873 for (Ring incomingRing : newSubGraph.getRings())
1874 {
1875 addRing(incomingRing);
1876 }
1877
1878 // import symmetric sets from incoming graph? No, this method doesn't do
1879 // it because we want to use it in situations where we have to perform
1880 // multiple replaceSubGraph operations and, afterwards, use the
1881 // symmetric labels to create symmetric sets that might span across
1882 // more than one of the subgraphs that were added.
1883
1884 // We keep track of the APs on the new link that have been dealt with
1885 List<AttachmentPoint> doneApsOnNew =
1886 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
1887
1888 // Connect the incoming subgraph to the rest of the graph
1889 if (trgAPOnNewLink != null)
1890 {
1891 // the incoming graph has a parent vertex, and the edge should be
1892 // directed accordingly
1893 Edge edge = new Edge(
1894 linksToRecreate.get(trgAPOnNewLink),
1895 trgAPOnNewLink,
1896 linkTypesToRecreate.get(trgAPOnNewLink));
1897 addEdge(edge);
1898 doneApsOnNew.add(trgAPOnNewLink);
1899 } else {
1900 // newLink does NOT have a parent vertex, so all the
1901 // edges see newLink as target vertex. Such links are dealt with
1902 // in the loop below. So, there is nothing special to do, here.
1903 }
1904 for (AttachmentPoint apOnNew : linksToRecreate.keySet())
1905 {
1906 if (apOnNew == trgAPOnNewLink)
1907 {
1908 continue; //done just before this loop
1909 }
1910 AttachmentPoint trgOnChild = linksToRecreate.get(apOnNew);
1911 Edge edge = new Edge(apOnNew,trgOnChild,
1912 linkTypesToRecreate.get(apOnNew));
1913 addEdge(edge);
1914 doneApsOnNew.add(apOnNew);
1915 }
1916
1917 // redefine rings that spanned over the removed subgraph
1918 for (Ring r : ringsOverSubGraph.keySet())
1919 {
1920 List<Vertex> vPair = ringsOverSubGraph.get(r);
1921 PathSubGraph path = new PathSubGraph(vPair.get(0),vPair.get(1),this);
1922 int initialInsertPoint = r.getPositionOf(vPair.get(0));
1923 List<Vertex> verticesInPath = path.getVertecesPath();
1924 for (int i=1; i<(verticesInPath.size()-1); i++)
1925 {
1926 r.insertVertex(initialInsertPoint+i, verticesInPath.get(i));
1927 }
1928 }
1929
1930 // update the mapping of this vertices' APs in the jacket template
1931 if (templateJacket != null)
1932 {
1933 templateJacket.clearIAtomContainer();
1934 for (AttachmentPoint apOnNew : inToOutAPForTemplate.keySet())
1935 {
1936 templateJacket.updateInnerApID(
1937 inToOutAPForTemplate.get(apOnNew),apOnNew);
1938 doneApsOnNew.add(apOnNew);
1939 }
1940
1941 // Project all remaining APs of new branch on the surface of template
1942 for (AttachmentPoint apOnNew : interfaceApsOnNewBranch)
1943 {
1944 if (!doneApsOnNew.contains(apOnNew))
1945 {
1946 templateJacket.addInnerToOuterAPMapping(apOnNew);
1947 }
1948 }
1949
1950 // Remove all APs that existed only in the old branch
1951 for (AttachmentPoint apOnOld : oldAPToRemoveFromTmpl)
1952 {
1953 templateJacket.removeProjectionOfInnerAP(apOnOld);
1954 }
1955 }
1956
1957 jGraph = null;
1958 jGraphKernel = null;
1959
1960 for (Vertex vOld : subGrpVrtxs)
1961 if (this.containsVertex(vOld))
1962 return false;
1963 for (Vertex vNew : newvertices)
1964 if (!this.containsVertex(vNew))
1965 return false;
1966 return true;
1967 }

1995
2011 public boolean replaceVertex(Vertex vertex, int bbId, BBType bbt,
2012 LinkedHashMap<Integer, Integer> apIdMap, boolean symmetry,
2013 FragmentSpace fragSpace)
2014 throws DENOPTIMException
2015 {
2016 if (!gVertices.contains(vertex))
2017 {
2018 return false;
2019 }
2020
2021 ArrayList<Vertex> symSites = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
2022 if (symmetry)
2023 {
2024 symSites = getSymVerticesForVertex(vertex);
2025 }
2026 if (symSites.size() == 0)
2027 {
2028 symSites.add(vertex);
2029 }
2030
2031 GraphUtils.ensureVertexIDConsistency(this.getMaxVertexId());
2032 Vertex newLink = Vertex.newVertexFromLibrary(
2033 GraphUtils.getUniqueVertexIndex(), bbId, bbt, fragSpace);
2034 DGraph incomingGraph = new DGraph();
2035 incomingGraph.addVertex(newLink);
2036 incomingGraph.reassignSymmetricLabels();
2037
2038 for (Vertex oldLink : symSites)
2039 {
2040 DGraph graphAdded = incomingGraph.clone();
2041 graphAdded.getVertexAtPosition(0).setMutationTypes(
2042 oldLink.getUnfilteredMutationTypes());
2043 graphAdded.renumberGraphVertices();
2044
2045 ArrayList<Vertex> oldVertex = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
2046 oldVertex.add(oldLink);
2047 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apMap =
2048 new LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>();
2049 for (Map.Entry<Integer,Integer> e : apIdMap.entrySet())
2050 {
2051 apMap.put(oldLink.getAP(e.getKey()),
2052 graphAdded.getVertexAtPosition(0).getAP(e.getValue()));
2053 }
2054
2055 if (!replaceSingleSubGraph(oldVertex, graphAdded, apMap))
2056 {
2057 return false;
2058 }
2059 }
2060 convertSymmetricLabelsToSymmetricSets();
2061 return true;
2062 }

2087 //NB: LinkedHashMap is used to retain reproducibility between runs.
2088
2089 public boolean insertVertex(Edge edge, int bbId, BBType bbt,
2090 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,Integer> apMap,
2091 FragmentSpace fragSpace)
2092 throws DENOPTIMException
2093 {
2094 if (!gEdges.contains(edge))
2095 {
2096 return false;
2097 }
2098
2099 ArrayList<Edge> symSites = new ArrayList<Edge> ();
2100 ArrayList<LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,Integer>> symApMaps =
2101 new ArrayList<LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,Integer>>();
2102 ArrayList<Vertex> symTrgvertices = getSymVerticesForVertex(
2103 edge.getTrgAP().getOwner());
2104 if (symTrgvertices.size() == 0)
2105 {
2106 symSites.add(edge);
2107 symApMaps.add(apMap);
2108 } else {
2109 for (Vertex trgVrtx : symTrgvertices)
2110 {
2111 Edge symEdge = trgVrtx.getEdgeToParent();
2112 symSites.add(symEdge);
2113
2114 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,Integer> locApMap = new
2115 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,Integer>();
2116 locApMap.put(symEdge.getSrcAP(), apMap.get(edge.getSrcAP()));
2117 locApMap.put(symEdge.getTrgAP(), apMap.get(edge.getTrgAP()));
2118 symApMaps.add(locApMap);
2119 }
2120 }
2121
2122 SymmetricSet newSS = new SymmetricSet();
2123 for (int i=0; i<symSites.size(); i++)
2124 {
2125 Edge symEdge = symSites.get(i);
2126 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,Integer> locApMap = symApMaps.get(i);
2127
2128 GraphUtils.ensureVertexIDConsistency(this.getMaxVertexId());
2129 Vertex newLink = Vertex.newVertexFromLibrary(
2130 GraphUtils.getUniqueVertexIndex(), bbId, bbt, fragSpace);
2131 newSS.add(newLink.getVertexId());
2132 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apToApMap =
2133 new LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>();
2134 for (AttachmentPoint apOnGraph : locApMap.keySet())
2135 {
2136 apToApMap.put(apOnGraph, newLink.getAP(locApMap.get(apOnGraph)));
2137 }
2138 if (!insertSingleVertex(symEdge, newLink, apToApMap))
2139 {
2140 return false;
2141 }
2142 }
2143 if (newSS.size()>1)
2144 {
2145 addSymmetricSetOfVertices(newSS);
2146 }
2147 return true;
2148 }

2150//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2151
2169 public boolean insertSingleVertex(Edge edge, Vertex newLink,
2170 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apMap)
2171 throws DENOPTIMException
2172 {
2173 //TODO: for reproducibility the AP mapping should become an optional
2174 // parameter: if given we try to use it, if not given we GraphLinkFinder
2175 // will try to find a suitable mapping.
2176
2177 if (!gEdges.contains(edge) || gVertices.contains(newLink))
2178 {
2179 return false;
2180 }
2181
2182 // First keep track of the links that will be broken and re-created,
2183 // and also of the relation free APs may have with a possible template
2184 // that embeds this graph.
2185 AttachmentPoint orisEdgeSrc = edge.getSrcAP();
2186 AttachmentPoint orisEdgeTrg = edge.getTrgAP();
2187 Vertex srcVrtx = orisEdgeSrc.getOwner();
2188 Vertex trgVrtx = orisEdgeTrg.getOwner();
2189
2190 removeEdge(edge);
2191
2192 // Introduce the new vertex in the graph
2193 addVertex(newLink);
2194
2195 // Connect the new vertex to the graph
2196 Edge eSrcToLink = new Edge(orisEdgeSrc,
2197 apMap.get(orisEdgeSrc), edge.getBondType());
2198 addEdge(eSrcToLink);
2199 Edge eLinkToTrg = new Edge(apMap.get(orisEdgeTrg),
2200 orisEdgeTrg, edge.getBondType());
2201 addEdge(eLinkToTrg);
2202
2203 // update any affected ring
2204 if (isVertexInRing(srcVrtx) && isVertexInRing(trgVrtx))
2205 {
2206 ArrayList<Ring> rToEdit = new ArrayList<Ring>();
2207 rToEdit.addAll(getRingsInvolvingVertex(srcVrtx));
2208 rToEdit.retainAll(getRingsInvolvingVertex(trgVrtx));
2209 for (Ring r : rToEdit)
2210 {
2211 r.insertVertex(newLink,srcVrtx,trgVrtx);
2212 }
2213 }
2214
2215 // NB: if this graph is embedded in a template, new free/available
2216 // APs introduced with the new link need to be mapped on the surface of
2217 // the template
2218 if (templateJacket != null)
2219 {
2220 for (AttachmentPoint ap : newLink.getAttachmentPoints())
2221 {
2222 if (ap.isAvailable())
2223 {
2224 templateJacket.addInnerToOuterAPMapping(ap);
2225 }
2226 }
2227 }
2228
2229 jGraph = null;
2230 jGraphKernel = null;
2231
2232 return !gEdges.contains(edge) && this.containsVertex(newLink);
2233 }

2723 public boolean directedPathExists(Vertex src, Vertex trg)
2724 {

2932 @Override
2933 public DGraph clone()
2934 {
2935 // When cloning, the VertexID remains the same so we'll have two
2936 // deep-copies of the same vertex having the same VertexID
2937 ArrayList<Vertex> cListVrtx = new ArrayList<>();
2938 Map<Integer,Vertex> vidsInClone =
2939 new HashMap<Integer,Vertex>();
2940 for (Vertex vOrig : gVertices)

3207 /*

3224

3226 new HashMap<Vertex,Set<Vertex>>();
3227
3228 @Override
3229 public int compare(Vertex v1, Vertex v2) {
3230
3231 // exploit symmetric relations between vertices
3232 if (symmetryShortCuts.containsKey(v1)
3233 && symmetryShortCuts.get(v1).contains(v2))
3234 {

3239 // an int to allow comparison.

3245 for (Integer sVrtId : ssV2.getList())

3262 } else {
3263 symmetryShortCuts.put(v1s,symToV2);
3264 }

3267 } else {

3272 v2.getBuildingBlockId());

3426 public boolean sameAs(DGraph other, StringBuilder reason)
3427 {
3428 if (this.getEdgeCount() != other.getEdgeCount())
3429 {
3430 reason.append("Different number of edges ("+this.getEdgeCount()+":"
3431 +other.getEdgeCount()+")");
3432 return false;
3433 }
3434
3435 if (this.getVertexCount() != other.getVertexCount())
3436 {
3437 reason.append("Different number of vertices ("+this.getVertexCount()+":"
3438 +other.getVertexCount()+")");
3439 return false;
3440 }
3441
3442 if (this.getSymmetricSetCount() != other.getSymmetricSetCount())
3443 {
3444 reason.append("Different number of symmetric sets ("
3445 + this.getSymmetricSetCount() + ":"
3446 + other.getSymmetricSetCount() + ")");
3447 return false;
3448 }
3449
3450 if (this.getRingCount() != other.getRingCount())
3451 {
3452 reason.append("Different number of Rings ("+this.getRingCount()+":"
3453 +other.getRingCount()+")");
3454 return false;
3455 }
3456
3457 //Pairwise correspondence of vertices
3458 Map<Vertex,Vertex> vertexMap =
3459 new HashMap<Vertex,Vertex>();
3460
3461 vertexMap.put(this.getVertexAtPosition(0),other.getVertexAtPosition(0));
3462
3463 //WARNING: assuming that the first vertex in the vertex list is the root
3464 // and also that there are no disconnections. Both assumptions are
3465 // reasonable for graphs.
3466 try {
3467 if (!compareGraphNodes(this.getVertexAtPosition(0), this,
3468 other.getVertexAtPosition(0), other,
3469 vertexMap,reason))
3470 {
3471 return false;
3472 }
3473 } catch (DENOPTIMException e) {
3474 e.printStackTrace();
3475 reason.append("Exception");
3476 return false;
3477 }
3478
3479 //Check Symmetric sets
3480 Iterator<SymmetricSet> ssIter = this.getSymSetsIterator();
3481 while (ssIter.hasNext())
3482 {
3483 SymmetricSet ssT = ssIter.next();
3484 int vIdT = ssT.get(0);
3485
3486 SymmetricSet ssO = other.getSymSetForVertexID(
3487 vertexMap.get(this.getVertexWithId(vIdT)).getVertexId());
3488 if (ssO.size() == 0)
3489 {
3490 // ssO is empty because no SymmetricSet was found that
3491 // contains the given vertexID. This means the two graphs
3492 // are different
3493 reason.append("Symmetric set not found for vertex ("+vIdT+")");
3494 return false;
3495 }
3496
3497 if (ssT.size() != ssO.size())
3498 {
3499 reason.append("Different number of symmetric sets on vertex " + vIdT
3500 + "("+ssT.size()+":"+ssO.size()+")");
3501 return false;
3502 }
3503
3504 for (int it=0; it<ssT.size(); it++)
3505 {
3506 int svIdT = ssT.get(it);
3507 if (!ssO.contains(vertexMap.get(this.getVertexWithId(svIdT))
3508 .getVertexId()))
3509 {
3510 reason.append("Difference in symmetric set ("+svIdT
3511 +" not in other)");
3512 return false;
3513 }
3514 }
3515 }
3516
3517 //Check Rings
3518 for (Ring rT : this.getRings())
3519 {
3520 Vertex vhT = rT.getHeadVertex();
3521 Vertex vtT = rT.getTailVertex();
3522 boolean hasRing = other
3523 .getRingsInvolvingVertex(vertexMap.get(vhT))
3524 .stream()
3525 .anyMatch(rO -> sameAsRings(reason, vertexMap, rT, vhT,
3526 vtT, rO));
3527 if (!hasRing) {
3528 return false;
3529 }
3530 }
3531
3532 return true;
3533 }

3535//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3536
3537 private boolean sameAsRings(StringBuilder reason, Map<Vertex,
3538 Vertex> vertexMap, Ring rT, Vertex vhT,
3539 Vertex vtT, Ring rO) {
3540 if (rT.getSize() != rO.getSize()) {
3541 reason.append("Different ring size (").append(rT.getSize())
3542 .append(":").append(rO.getSize()).append(")");
3543 return false;
3544 }
3545
3546 if (rO.getHeadVertex() == vertexMap.get(vhT)
3547 && rO.getTailVertex() == vertexMap.get(vtT)) {
3548 for (int i = 1; i < rT.getSize(); i++) {
3549 if (vertexMap.get(rT.getVertexAtPosition(i))
3550 != rO.getVertexAtPosition(i)) {
3551 reason.append("Rings differ (A) (").append(rT).append(":")
3552 .append(rO).append(")");
3553 return false;
3554 }
3555 }
3556 } else if (rO.getHeadVertex() == vertexMap.get(vtT)
3557 && rO.getTailVertex() == vertexMap.get(vhT)) {
3558 for (int i = 1; i < rT.getSize(); i++) {
3559 int j = rO.getSize() - i - 1;
3560 if (vertexMap.get(rT.getVertexAtPosition(i))
3561 != rO.getVertexAtPosition(j)) {
3562 reason.append("Rings differ (B) (").append(rT).append(":")
3563 .append(rO).append(")");
3564 return false;
3565 }
3566 }
3567 } else {
3568 reason.append("Rings differ (C) (").append(rT).append(":")
3569 .append(rO).append(")");
3570 return false;
3571 }
3572 return true;
3573 }

3611 private static boolean compareGraphNodes(Vertex seedOnA,
3612 DGraph gA, Vertex seedOnB, DGraph gB,
3613 Map<Vertex,Vertex> vertexMap, StringBuilder reason)
3614 throws DENOPTIMException
3615 {
3616 if (!seedOnA.sameAs(seedOnB, reason))
3617 {
3618 reason.append("Different vertex ("+seedOnA+":"+seedOnB+")");
3619 return false;
3620 }
3621
3622 ArrayList<Edge> edgesFromThis = gA.getEdgesWithSrc(seedOnA);
3623 ArrayList<Edge> edgesFromOther = gB.getEdgesWithSrc(seedOnB);
3624 if (edgesFromThis.size() != edgesFromOther.size())
3625 {
3626 reason.append("Different number of edges from vertex "+seedOnA+" ("
3627 +edgesFromThis.size()+":"
3628 +edgesFromOther.size()+")");
3629 return false;
3630 }
3631
3632 // pairwise correspondence between child vertices
3633 ArrayList<Vertex[]> pairs = new ArrayList<Vertex[]>();
3634
3635 for (Edge et : edgesFromThis)
3636 {
3637 boolean found = false;
3638 Edge eo = null;
3639 StringBuilder innerSb = new StringBuilder();
3640 int otherEdgeI = 0;
3641 for (Edge e : edgesFromOther)
3642 {
3643 innerSb.append(" Edge"+otherEdgeI+":");
3644 if (et.sameAs(e,innerSb))
3645 {
3646 found = true;
3647 eo = e;
3648 break;
3649 }
3650 }
3651 if (!found)
3652 {
3653 reason.append("Edge not found in other("+et+"). "
3654 + "Edges in othes: "+innerSb.toString());
3655 return false;
3656 }
3657
3658 //Check: this should never be true
3659 if (vertexMap.keySet().contains(
3660 gA.getVertexWithId(et.getTrgVertex())))
3661 {
3662 throw new DENOPTIMException("More than one attempt to set vertex map.");
3663 }
3664 vertexMap.put(gA.getVertexWithId(et.getTrgVertex()),
3665 gB.getVertexWithId(eo.getTrgVertex()));
3666
3667 Vertex[] pair = new Vertex[]{
3668 gA.getVertexWithId(et.getTrgVertex()),
3669 gB.getVertexWithId(eo.getTrgVertex())};
3670 pairs.add(pair);
3671 }
3672
3673 //Recursion on child vertices
3674 for (Vertex[] pair : pairs)
3675 {
3676 Vertex v = pair[0];
3677 Vertex o = pair[1];
3678 boolean localRes = compareGraphNodes(v, gA, o, gB,vertexMap,
3679 reason);
3680 if (!localRes)
3681 {
3682 return false;
3683 }
3684 }
3685
3686 return true;
3687 }

3924 public void addCappingGroups(List<Vertex> vertexAddedToThis,

3926 {

3928 return;

3933 // to have only one AP, there should never be a capping group with
3934 // a free AP.

3936 {

3938 }

3940 for (AttachmentPoint curDap : curVertex.getAttachmentPoints())

3945 curDap.getAPClass());

3947 {
3948 int bbIdCap = fragSpace.getCappingFragment(apcCap);
3949
3950 if (bbIdCap != -1)
3951 {
3952 Vertex capVrtx = Vertex.newVertexFromLibrary(
3953 GraphUtils.getUniqueVertexIndex(),
3954 bbIdCap, BBType.CAP, fragSpace);
3955 DGraph molGraph = curDap.getOwner()
3956 .getGraphOwner();
3957 if (molGraph == null)
3958 throw new Error("Cannot add capping "
3959 + "groups to a vertex that does not "
3960 + "belong to a graph.");
3961 molGraph.appendVertexOnAP(curDap, capVrtx.getAP(0));
3962 }
3963 else
3964 {
3965 String msg = "Capping is required but no proper "
3966 + "capping fragment found with APCalss "
3967 + apcCap;

3969 }
3970 }

4217
4225 public List<DGraph> extractPattern(GraphPattern pattern)
4226 throws DENOPTIMException
4227 {
4228 if (pattern != GraphPattern.RING) {
4229 throw new IllegalArgumentException("Graph pattern " + pattern +
4230 " not supported.");
4231 }
4232
4233 List<Set<Vertex>> disjointMultiCycleVertices = this
4234 .getRings()
4235 .stream()
4236 .map(Ring::getVertices)
4237 .map(HashSet::new)
4238 .collect(Collectors.toList());
4239
4240 GeneralUtils.unionOfIntersectingSets(disjointMultiCycleVertices);
4241
4242 List<DGraph> subgraphs = new ArrayList<>();
4243 for (Set<Vertex> fusedRing : disjointMultiCycleVertices) {
4244 subgraphs.add(extractSubgraph(fusedRing));
4245 }
4246
4247 for (DGraph g : subgraphs) {
4248 g.storeCurrentVertexIDs();
4249 g.renumberGraphVertices();
4250 reorderVertexList(g);
4251 }
4252
4253 return subgraphs;
4254 }

4266 private DGraph extractSubgraph(Set<Vertex> definedOn)
4267 {
4268 DGraph subgraph = this.clone();
4269
4270 Set<Vertex> complement = subgraph
4271 .getVertexList()
4272 .stream()
4273 .filter(u -> definedOn
4274 .stream()
4275 .allMatch(v -> v.getVertexId() != u.getVertexId())
4276 ).collect(Collectors.toSet());
4277
4278 for (Vertex v : complement) {
4279 subgraph.removeVertex(v);
4280 }
4281 return subgraph;
4282 }

4295 {

4298 return;

4304//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4305
4310 private static void fixEdgeDirections(DGraph graph)
4311 {
4312 Vertex src = graph.getSourceVertex();
4313 fixEdgeDirections(src, new HashSet<>());
4314 }
4315
4316//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4317
4322 private static void fixEdgeDirections(Vertex v,
4323 Set<Integer> visited)
4324 {
4325 visited.add(v.getVertexId());
4326 int visitedVertexEncounters = 0;
4327 for (int i = 0; i < v.getNumberOfAPs(); i++) {
4328 AttachmentPoint ap = v.getAP(i);
4329 Edge edge = ap.getEdgeUser();
4330 if (edge != null) {
4331 int srcVertex = edge.getSrcVertex();
4332 boolean srcIsVisited =
4333 srcVertex != v.getVertexId()
4334 && visited.contains(srcVertex);
4335
4336 visitedVertexEncounters += srcIsVisited ? 1 : 0;
4337 if (visitedVertexEncounters >= 2) {
4338 throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid graph. "
4339 + "Contains a cycle.");
4340 }
4341
4342 boolean edgeIsWrongWay = edge.getTrgVertex()
4343 == v.getVertexId() && !srcIsVisited;
4344 if (edgeIsWrongWay) {
4345 edge.flipEdge();
4346 }
4347 if (!srcIsVisited) {
4348 fixEdgeDirections(edge.getTrgAP().getOwner(), visited);
4349 }
4350 }
4351 }
4352 }

4449//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4450
4462 public boolean removeChainUpToBranching(Vertex v,
4463 FragmentSpace fragSpace) throws DENOPTIMException
4464 {
4465 List<Ring> rings = getRingsInvolvingVertex(v);
4466 if (rings.isEmpty())
4467 {
4468 return false;
4469 }
4470
4471 // Identify the RCVs defining the chord that might become an edge
4472 // The corresponding ring is the "frame" we'll use throughout this
4473 // operation, and is the smallest ring that is closest to the appointed
4474 // vertex.
4475 Ring frame = null;
4476 Vertex[] replacedByEdge = new Vertex[2];
4477 int minDist = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
4478 BondType bt = null;
4479 for (Ring r : rings)
4480 {
4481 int dist = Math.min(r.getDistance(r.getHeadVertex(),v),
4482 r.getDistance(r.getTailVertex(),v));
4483 if (dist < minDist)
4484 {
4485 minDist = dist;
4486 frame = r;
4487 replacedByEdge[0] = r.getHeadVertex();
4488 replacedByEdge[1] = r.getTailVertex();
4489 bt = r.getBondType();
4490 }
4491 }
4492
4493 // Find out where branching vertices are along the frame ring
4494 boolean frameHasBranching = false;
4495 List<Integer> branchingPositions = new ArrayList<Integer>();
4496 int posOfFocusVrtInRing = frame.getPositionOf(v);
4497 for (int i=0; i<frame.getSize(); i++)
4498 {
4499 Vertex vi = frame.getVertexAtPosition(i);
4500 // We consider the scaffold as a branching point, i.e., it will never be removed
4501 if (vi.getBuildingBlockType() == BBType.SCAFFOLD)
4502 {
4503 branchingPositions.add(i);
4504 continue;
4505 }
4506 long oNonCap = vi.getAttachmentPoints().size()
4507 - vi.getCappedAPCountThroughout()
4508 - vi.getFreeAPCountThroughout();
4509 if (oNonCap > 2)
4510 {
4511 branchingPositions.add(i);
4512 frameHasBranching = true;
4513 }
4514 }
4515
4516 // Make sure this ring is not all there is in this graph.
4517 if (rings.size()==1 && !frameHasBranching)
4518 {
4519 return false;
4520 }
4521
4522 // Identify the end points of chain that gets removed, i.e., the chain
4523 // containing V and is between branchingDownstreamId and
4524 // branchingUpstreamId gets removed.
4525 int branchingDownstreamId = -1;
4526 for (int i=0; i<frame.getSize(); i++)
4527 {
4528 int iTranslated = i + posOfFocusVrtInRing;
4529 if (iTranslated >= frame.getSize())
4530 iTranslated = iTranslated - frame.getSize();
4531 if (branchingPositions.contains(iTranslated))
4532 {
4533 branchingDownstreamId = iTranslated;
4534 break;
4535 }
4536 }
4537 int branchingUpstreamId = -1;
4538 for (int i=(frame.getSize()-1); i>-1; i--)
4539 {
4540 int iTranslated = i + posOfFocusVrtInRing;
4541 if (iTranslated >= frame.getSize())
4542 iTranslated = iTranslated - frame.getSize();
4543 if (branchingPositions.contains(iTranslated))
4544 {
4545 branchingUpstreamId = iTranslated;
4546 break;
4547 }
4548 }
4549
4550 // Now, collect the vertices along the ring based on whether they
4551 // will be removed or remain (possible with a change of edge direction
4552 // and replacement of an RCV pair by edge)
4553 List<Vertex> remainingChain = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
4554 for (int i=0; i<frame.getSize(); i++)
4555 {
4556 int iTranslated = i + branchingDownstreamId;
4557 if (iTranslated >= frame.getSize())
4558 iTranslated = iTranslated - frame.getSize();
4559 remainingChain.add(frame.getVertexAtPosition(iTranslated));
4560 if (iTranslated == branchingUpstreamId)
4561 {
4562 break;
4563 }
4564 }
4565 List<Vertex> toRemoveChain = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
4566 for (int i=0; i<frame.getSize(); i++)
4567 {
4568 int iTranslated = i + branchingUpstreamId + 1; //exclude branch point
4569 if (iTranslated >= frame.getSize())
4570 iTranslated = iTranslated - frame.getSize();
4571 toRemoveChain.add(frame.getVertexAtPosition(iTranslated));
4572 if (iTranslated == (branchingDownstreamId - 1)) //exclude branch point
4573 {
4574 break;
4575 }
4576 }
4577
4578 // Need to exclude the case where the chain to remove consists only of
4579 // the RCVs because it would lead to loss of the chord and creation of
4580 // cyclic graph. Also, proceeding without making the edge would simply
4581 // correspond to removing the chord.
4582 if (toRemoveChain.size() == 2)
4583 {
4584 int countOrRCVs = 0;
4585 for (Vertex vtr : toRemoveChain)
4586 {
4587 if (vtr.isRCV())
4588 countOrRCVs++;
4589 }
4590 if (countOrRCVs == 2)
4591 {
4592 return false;
4593 }
4594 }
4595
4596 // To understand if we need to reverse some edges, we identify the
4597 // deepest vertex level-wise. It may or may not be a scaffold!!!
4598 int deepestLevel = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
4599 Vertex deepestVrtRemainingChain = null;
4600 for (Vertex vint : remainingChain)
4601 {
4602 int lvl = getLevel(vint);
4603 if (lvl < deepestLevel)
4604 {
4605 deepestLevel = lvl;
4606 deepestVrtRemainingChain = vint;
4607 }
4608 }
4609
4610 // Check if we need to transform a pair of RCVs into an edge, and
4611 // identify APs used by the edge that replaces the to-be-removed RCVs.
4612 // I do not see how the chain can possibly contain only one of the
4613 // RCVs, so I assume that if one RCV is there, then the other is too.
4614 if (remainingChain.contains(replacedByEdge[0]))
4615 {
4616 AttachmentPoint apSrcOfNewEdge = replacedByEdge[0]
4617 .getEdgeToParent().getSrcAP();
4618 AttachmentPoint apTrgOfNewEdge = replacedByEdge[1]
4619 .getEdgeToParent().getSrcAP();
4620
4621 // Remove the RCVs that will be replaced by an edge
4622 removeVertex(replacedByEdge[0]);
4623 remainingChain.remove(replacedByEdge[0]);
4624 removeVertex(replacedByEdge[1]);
4625 remainingChain.remove(replacedByEdge[1]);
4626
4627 // And make the new edge. The direction can be anything. Later, we
4628 // decide if we need to reverse it.
4629 //NB: the compatibility between the APs should be granted by the
4630 // previous existence of the chord. so no need to check
4631 // apSrcOfNewEdge.getAPClass().isCPMapCompatibleWith(
4632 // apTrgOfNewEdge.getAPClass()))
4633 addEdge(new Edge(apSrcOfNewEdge, apTrgOfNewEdge, bt));
4634 } else {
4635 // We remove the frame already, otherwise we will try to recreate
4636 // such ring from RCVs and waste time with it.
4637 removeRing(frame);
4638 }
4639
4640 // Now, inspect the paths from the deepest vertex and outwards, to
4641 // find out where to start reversing edges.
4642 List<Vertex> chainToReverseA = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
4643 List<Vertex> chainToReverseB = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
4644 for (int i=(remainingChain.indexOf(deepestVrtRemainingChain)+1);
4645 i<remainingChain.size(); i++)
4646 {
4647 Vertex vPrev = remainingChain.get(i-1);
4648 Vertex vHere = remainingChain.get(i);
4649 if (!vPrev.getChilddren().contains(vHere))
4650 {
4651 // in an healthy spanning tree, once we find the first reversed
4652 // edge, all the following edges will also have to be reversed.
4653 if (chainToReverseA.size()==0)
4654 chainToReverseA.add(vPrev);
4655 chainToReverseA.add(vHere);
4656 }
4657 }
4658 for (int i=(remainingChain.indexOf(deepestVrtRemainingChain)-1);i>-1;i--)
4659 {
4660 Vertex vPrev = remainingChain.get(i+1);
4661 Vertex vHere = remainingChain.get(i);
4662 if (!vPrev.getChilddren().contains(vHere))
4663 {
4664 if (chainToReverseB.size()==0)
4665 chainToReverseB.add(vPrev);
4666 chainToReverseB.add(vHere);
4667 }
4668 }
4669
4670 // These are to remember all chords that will have to be recreated
4671 LinkedHashMap<Vertex,Vertex> chordsToRecreate =
4672 new LinkedHashMap<Vertex,Vertex>();
4673 LinkedHashMap<Vertex,BondType> chordsToRecreateBB =
4674 new LinkedHashMap<Vertex,BondType>();
4675
4676 // Change direction of those edges that have to be reversed as a
4677 // consequence of the change in the spanning tree.
4678 if (chainToReverseA.size()+chainToReverseB.size() > 1)
4679 {
4680 List<Vertex> chainToWorkOn = null;
4681 for (int ic=0; ic<2; ic++)
4682 {
4683 if (ic == 1)
4684 chainToWorkOn = chainToReverseA;
4685 else
4686 chainToWorkOn = chainToReverseB;
4687
4688 for (int i=1; i<chainToWorkOn.size(); i++)
4689 {
4690 Vertex vHere = chainToWorkOn.get(i);
4691 Vertex vPrev = chainToWorkOn.get(i-1);
4692 List<Ring> ringsToRecreate = new ArrayList<>();
4693 for (Ring r : getRingsInvolvingVertex(vHere))
4694 {
4695 ringsToRecreate.add(r);
4696 chordsToRecreate.put(r.getHeadVertex(),
4697 r.getTailVertex());
4698 chordsToRecreateBB.put(r.getHeadVertex(),
4699 r.getBondType());
4700 }
4701 for (Ring r : ringsToRecreate)
4702 {
4703 removeRing(r);
4704 }
4705
4706 Edge edgeToPrevious = vHere.getEdgeWith(vPrev);
4707 if (edgeToPrevious == null)
4708 {
4709 // Since we have already made the new edge this should
4710 // never happen.
4711 String debugFile = "debug_"+v.getVertexId()+".json";
4712 DenoptimIO.writeGraphToJSON(new File(debugFile), this);
4713 throw new DENOPTIMException("Unconnected vertices "
4714 + vHere.getVertexId() + " and "
4715 + vPrev.getVertexId() + ". Unable to deal with "
4716 + "removal of " + v + " from ring " + frame
4717 + " in graph " + this.getGraphId()
4718 + ". See graph in " + debugFile);
4719 } else {
4720 if (edgeToPrevious.getSrcAP().getOwner() == vHere)
4721 {
4722 // This is an edge that has to be reversed.
4723 AttachmentPoint newSrcAP =
4724 edgeToPrevious.getTrgAP();
4725 AttachmentPoint newTrgAP =
4726 edgeToPrevious.getSrcAP();
4727 if (newSrcAP.getAPClass().isCPMapCompatibleWith(
4728 newTrgAP.getAPClass(), fragSpace))
4729 {
4730 BondType oldBt = edgeToPrevious.getBondType();
4731 removeEdge(edgeToPrevious);
4732 addEdge(new Edge(newSrcAP, newTrgAP,
4733 oldBt));
4734 } else {
4735 // There is a non-reversible connection along
4736 // the way, therefore we cannot do this
4737 // specific mutation.
4738 return false;
4739 }
4740 }
4741 }
4742 }
4743 }
4744 }
4745
4746 // Delete the chain to be removed
4747 for (Vertex vtr : toRemoveChain)
4748 {
4749 // This works across template boundaries!
4750 for (Vertex child : vtr.getChildrenThroughout())
4751 {
4752 if (remainingChain.contains(child)
4753 || toRemoveChain.contains(child))
4754 continue;
4755 DGraph ownerOfChild = child.getGraphOwner();
4756 ownerOfChild.removeVertex(child);
4757 }
4758 if (templateJacket!= null)
4759 {
4760 List<AttachmentPoint> apProjectionsToRemove =
4761 new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
4762 for (AttachmentPoint outerAP :
4763 templateJacket.getAttachmentPoints())
4764 {
4765 AttachmentPoint innerAP =
4766 templateJacket.getInnerAPFromOuterAP(outerAP);
4767 if (innerAP.getOwner() == vtr)
4768 {
4769 apProjectionsToRemove.add(innerAP);
4770 }
4771 }
4772 for (AttachmentPoint apToRemove : apProjectionsToRemove)
4773 templateJacket.removeProjectionOfInnerAP(apToRemove);
4774 }
4775 removeVertex(vtr);
4776 }
4777
4778 // Regenerate the rings that have been affected
4779 for (Vertex h : chordsToRecreate.keySet())
4780 {
4781 addRing(h, chordsToRecreate.get(h), chordsToRecreateBB.get(h));
4782 }
4783
4784 // Symmetry relation need to be compared with the change of topology.
4785 // The worst that can happen is that two vertices that are
4786 // listed as symmetric are, instead, one the (grand)parent of
4787 // the other. This is inconsistent with the expectations when
4788 // dealing with any operation with symmetric vertices.
4789 // A different level does NOT imply a parent-child relation,
4790 // but is a sign that the topology has changed substantially,
4791 // and that the symmetric relation is, most likely, not sensible
4792 // anymore.
4793 List<SymmetricSet> ssToRemove = new ArrayList<SymmetricSet>();
4794 Iterator<SymmetricSet> ssIter = getSymSetsIterator();
4795 while (ssIter.hasNext())
4796 {
4797 SymmetricSet ss = ssIter.next();
4798 int level = -2;
4799 for (Integer vid : ss.getList())
4800 {
4801 if (level==-2)
4802 {
4803 level = getLevel(getVertexWithId(vid));
4804 } else {
4805 if (level != getLevel(getVertexWithId(vid)))
4806 {
4807 ssToRemove.add(ss);
4808 break;
4809 }
4810 }
4811 }
4812 }
4813 for (SymmetricSet ss : ssToRemove)
4814 removeSymmetrySet(ss);
4815
4816 // The free-ed up APs need to be projected to template's surface
4817 if (templateJacket!= null)
4818 {
4819 for (AttachmentPoint innerAP : getAvailableAPs())
4820 {
4821 templateJacket.addInnerToOuterAPMapping(innerAP);
4822 }
4823 }
4824
4825 return true;
4826 }

4893 {

4902
4903 nmap.put(vid, nvid);
4904
4905 v.setVertexId(nvid);
4906 v.setProperty(DENOPTIMConstants.STOREDVID, vid);

4910 Iterator<SymmetricSet> iter = getSymSetsIterator();

4915 {
4916 if (!nmap.containsKey(ss.getList().get(i)))
4917 {
4918 DENOPTIMException e = new DENOPTIMException("Assumption "
4919 + "violated: vertex IDs in "
4920 + "symmetric set are out of sync w.r.t. actual "
4921 + "vertex IDs. Report bug!");
4922 throw e;
4923 }
4924 ss.getList().set(i,nmap.get(ss.getList().get(i)));
4925 }
4926 }

4974//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4975
4999 public Object[] checkConsistency(RunTimeParameters settings, boolean permissive)
5000 throws DENOPTIMException
5001 {
5002 RingClosureParameters rcSettings = new RingClosureParameters();
5003 if (settings.containsParameters(ParametersType.RC_PARAMS))
5004 {
5005 rcSettings = (RingClosureParameters)settings.getParameters(
5006 ParametersType.RC_PARAMS);
5007 }
5008 FragmentSpaceParameters fsSettings = new FragmentSpaceParameters();
5009 if (settings.containsParameters(ParametersType.FS_PARAMS))
5010 {
5011 fsSettings = (FragmentSpaceParameters)settings.getParameters(
5012 ParametersType.FS_PARAMS);
5013 }
5014
5015 // calculate the molecule representation
5016 ThreeDimTreeBuilder t3d = new ThreeDimTreeBuilder(settings.getLogger(),
5017 settings.getRandomizer());
5018 t3d.setAlignBBsIn3D(false);
5019 IAtomContainer mol = t3d.convertGraphTo3DAtomContainer(this,true);
5020 if (mol == null)
5021 {
5022 String msg ="Evaluation of graph: graph-to-mol returned null!"
5023 + toString();
5024 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5025 return null;
5026 }
5027
5028 // check if the molecule is connected
5029 boolean isConnected = ConnectivityChecker.isConnected(mol);
5030 if (!isConnected)
5031 {
5032 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: Not all connected"
5033 + toString();
5034 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5035 return null;
5036 }
5037
5038 // SMILES
5039 String smiles = null;
5040 smiles = MoleculeUtils.getSMILESForMolecule(mol,settings.getLogger());
5041 if (smiles == null)
5042 {
5043 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: SMILES is null! "
5044 + toString();
5045 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5046 smiles = "FAIL: NO SMILES GENERATED";
5047 }
5048 // if by chance the smiles indicates a disconnected molecule
5049 if (smiles.contains(".") && !permissive)
5050 {
5051 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: SMILES contains \".\"" + smiles;
5052 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5053 return null;
5054 }
5055
5056 // criteria from definition of Fragment space
5057 // 1A) number of heavy atoms
5058 if (fsSettings.getMaxHeavyAtom()>0 && !permissive)
5059 {
5060 if (MoleculeUtils.getHeavyAtomCount(mol) >
5061 fsSettings.getMaxHeavyAtom())
5062 {
5063 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: Max atoms constraint "
5064 + " violated: " + smiles;
5065 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5066 return null;
5067 }
5068 }
5069
5070 // 1B) molecular weight
5071 double mw = MoleculeUtils.getMolecularWeight(mol);
5072 if (fsSettings.getMaxMW()>0 && !permissive)
5073 {
5074 if (mw > fsSettings.getMaxMW())
5075 {
5076 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: Molecular weight "
5077 + "constraint violated: " + smiles + " | MW: " + mw;
5078 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5079 return null;
5080 }
5081 }
5082 mol.setProperty("MOL_WT", mw);
5083
5084 // 1C) number of rotatable bonds
5085 int nrot = MoleculeUtils.getNumberOfRotatableBonds(mol);
5086 if (fsSettings.getMaxRotatableBond()>0 && !permissive)
5087 {
5088 if (nrot > fsSettings.getMaxRotatableBond())
5089 {
5090 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: Max rotatable bonds "
5091 + "constraint violated: "+ smiles;
5092 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5093 return null;
5094 }
5095 }
5096 mol.setProperty("ROT_BND", nrot);
5097
5098 // 1D) unacceptable free APs
5099 if (fsSettings.getFragmentSpace().useAPclassBasedApproach())
5100 {
5101 if (hasForbiddenEnd(fsSettings))
5102 {
5103 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: forbidden end in graph!";
5104 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5105 return null;
5106 }
5107 }
5108
5109 // criteria from settings of ring closures
5110 if (rcSettings.allowRingClosures() && !permissive)
5111 {
5112 // Count rings and RCAs
5113 int nPossRings = 0;
5114 Set<String> doneType = new HashSet<>();
5115 Map<String,String> rcaTypes = DENOPTIMConstants.RCATYPEMAP;
5116 for (String rcaTyp : rcaTypes.keySet())
5117 {
5118 if (doneType.contains(rcaTyp))
5119 {
5120 continue;
5121 }
5122
5123 int nThisType = 0;
5124 int nCompType = 0;
5125 for (Vertex v : getRCVertices())
5126 {
5127 if (v.containsAtoms())
5128 {
5129 IAtom atm = v.getIAtomContainer().getAtom(0);
5130 if (MoleculeUtils.getSymbolOrLabel(atm).equals(rcaTyp))
5131 {
5132 nThisType++;
5133 }
5134 else if (MoleculeUtils.getSymbolOrLabel(atm).equals(
5135 rcaTypes.get(rcaTyp)))
5136 {
5137 nCompType++;
5138 }
5139 }
5140 }
5141
5142 // check number of rca per type
5143 if (nThisType > rcSettings.getMaxRcaPerType(rcaTyp) ||
5144 nCompType > rcSettings.getMaxRcaPerType(rcaTyp))
5145 {
5146 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: too many RCAs! "
5147 + rcaTyp + ":" + nThisType + " "
5148 + rcaTypes.get(rcaTyp) + ":" + nCompType;
5149 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5150 return null;
5151 }
5152 if (nThisType < rcSettings.getMinRcaPerType(rcaTyp) ||
5153 nCompType < rcSettings.getMinRcaPerType(rcaTyp))
5154 {
5155 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: too few RCAs! "
5156 + rcaTyp + ":" + nThisType + " "
5157 + rcaTypes.get(rcaTyp) + ":" + nCompType;
5158 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5159 return null;
5160 }
5161
5162 nPossRings = nPossRings + Math.min(nThisType, nCompType);
5163 doneType.add(rcaTyp);
5164 doneType.add(rcaTypes.get(rcaTyp));
5165 }
5166 if (nPossRings < rcSettings.getMinRingClosures())
5167 {
5168 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: too few ring candidates";
5169 settings.getLogger().log(Level.FINE, msg);
5170 return null;
5171 }
5172 }
5173
5174 // get the smiles/Inchi representation
5175 String inchiKey = MoleculeUtils.getInChIKeyForMolecule(mol,
5176 settings.getLogger());
5177 if (inchiKey == null)
5178 {
5179 String msg = "Evaluation of graph: InChI Key is null!";
5180 settings.getLogger().log(Level.WARNING, msg);
5181 inchiKey = "UNDEFINED_INCHI";
5182 }
5183
5184 Object[] res = new Object[3];
5185 res[0] = inchiKey;
5186 res[1] = smiles;
5187 res[2] = mol;
5188
5189 return res;
5190 }

5201 public ArrayList<DGraph> makeAllGraphsWithDifferentRingSets(
5202 RunTimeParameters settings)
5203 throws DENOPTIMException
5204 {
5205 RingClosureParameters rcSettings = new RingClosureParameters();
5206 if (settings.containsParameters(ParametersType.RC_PARAMS))
5207 {
5208 rcSettings = (RingClosureParameters)settings.getParameters(
5209 ParametersType.RC_PARAMS);
5210 }
5211 FragmentSpaceParameters fsSettings = new FragmentSpaceParameters();
5212 if (settings.containsParameters(ParametersType.FS_PARAMS))
5213 {
5214 fsSettings = (FragmentSpaceParameters)settings.getParameters(
5215 ParametersType.FS_PARAMS);
5216 }
5217 ArrayList<DGraph> lstGraphs = new ArrayList<>();
5218
5219 boolean rcnEnabled = fsSettings.getFragmentSpace()
5220 .useAPclassBasedApproach();
5221 if (!rcnEnabled)
5222 return lstGraphs;
5223
5224 boolean evaluateRings = rcSettings.allowRingClosures();
5225 if (!evaluateRings)
5226 return lstGraphs;
5227
5228 // get a atoms/bonds molecular representation (no 3D needed)
5229 ThreeDimTreeBuilder t3d = new ThreeDimTreeBuilder(settings.getLogger(),
5230 settings.getRandomizer());
5231 t3d.setAlignBBsIn3D(false);
5232 IAtomContainer mol = t3d.convertGraphTo3DAtomContainer(this,false);
5233
5234 // Set rotatable property as property of IBond
5235 RotationalSpaceUtils.defineRotatableBonds(mol,
5236 fsSettings.getRotSpaceDefFile(), true, true,
5237 settings.getLogger());
5238
5239 // get the set of possible RCA combinations = ring closures
5240 CyclicGraphHandler cgh = new CyclicGraphHandler(rcSettings,
5241 fsSettings.getFragmentSpace());
5242 ArrayList<List<Ring>> allCombsOfRings =
5243 cgh.getPossibleCombinationOfRings(mol, this);
5244
5245 // Keep closable chains that are relevant for chelate formation
5246 if (rcSettings.buildChelatesMode())
5247 {
5248 ArrayList<List<Ring>> toRemove = new ArrayList<>();
5249 for (List<Ring> setRings : allCombsOfRings)
5250 {
5251 if (!cgh.checkChelatesGraph(this,setRings))
5252 {
5253 toRemove.add(setRings);
5254 }
5255 }
5256 allCombsOfRings.removeAll(toRemove);
5257 }
5258
5259 // prepare output graphs
5260 for (List<Ring> ringSet : allCombsOfRings)
5261 {
5262 // clone root graph
5263 DGraph newGraph = this.clone();
5264
5265 Map<Integer,Integer> vRenum = newGraph.renumberVerticesGetMap();
5266 newGraph.setGraphId(GraphUtils.getUniqueGraphIndex());
5267
5268 // add rings
5269 for (Ring oldRing : ringSet)
5270 {
5271 Ring newRing = new Ring();
5272 for (int i=0; i<oldRing.getSize(); i++)
5273 {
5274 int oldVId = oldRing.getVertexAtPosition(i).getVertexId();
5275 int newVId = vRenum.get(oldVId);
5276 newRing.addVertex(newGraph.getVertexWithId(newVId));
5277 }
5278 newRing.setBondType(oldRing.getBondType());
5279 newGraph.addRing(newRing);
5280 }
5281
5282 // store
5283 lstGraphs.add(newGraph);
5284 }
5285
5286 return lstGraphs;
5287 }

5298 public boolean hasForbiddenEnd(FragmentSpaceParameters fsSettings)
5299 {
5300 ArrayList<Vertex> vertices = getVertexList();
5301 Set<APClass> classOfForbEnds =
5302 fsSettings.getFragmentSpace().getForbiddenEndList();
5303 boolean found = false;
5304 for (Vertex vtx : vertices)
5305 {
5306 ArrayList<AttachmentPoint> daps = vtx.getAttachmentPoints();
5307 for (AttachmentPoint dp : daps)
5308 {
5309 if (dp.isAvailable())
5310 {
5311 APClass apClass = dp.getAPClass();
5312 if (classOfForbEnds.contains(apClass))
5313 {
5314 found = true;
5315 String msg = "Forbidden free AP for Vertex: "
5316 + vtx.getVertexId() + " "
5317 + vtx.toString()
5318 + "\n"+ this +" \n "
5319 + " AP class: " + apClass;
5320 fsSettings.getLogger().log(Level.WARNING, msg);
5321 break;
5322 }
5323 }
5324 }
5325 if (found)
5326 {
5327 break;
5328 }
5329 }
5330
5331 return found;
5332 }

5471
5492 public void appendGraphOnAP(Vertex parentVertex, int parentAPIdx,
5493 DGraph subGraph,
5494 Vertex childVertex, int childAPIdx,
5495 BondType bndType,
5496 Map<Integer,SymmetricSet> newSymSets)
5497 throws DENOPTIMException
5498 {
5499 // Clone and renumber the subgraph to ensure uniqueness
5500 DGraph sgClone = subGraph.clone();
5501 // The clones have the same vertex IDs before renumbering vertices
5502 Vertex cvClone = sgClone.getVertexWithId(
5503 childVertex.getVertexId());
5504 sgClone.renumberGraphVertices();
5505
5506 Edge edge = new Edge(parentVertex.getAP(parentAPIdx),
5507 cvClone.getAP(childAPIdx), bndType);
5508 addEdge(edge);
5509
5510 // Import all vertices from cloned subgraph, i.e., sgClone
5511 for (int i=0; i<sgClone.getVertexList().size(); i++)
5512 {
5513 Vertex clonV = sgClone.getVertexList().get(i);
5514 Vertex origV = subGraph.getVertexList().get(i);
5515
5516 addVertex(sgClone.getVertexList().get(i));
5517
5518 // also need to tmp store pointers to symmetric vertices
5519 // Why is this working on subGraph and not on sgClone?
5520 // Since we are only checking is there is symmetry, there should be
5521 // no difference between doing it on sgClone or subGraph.
5522 if (subGraph.hasSymmetryInvolvingVertex(origV))
5523 {
5524 if (newSymSets.containsKey(origV.getVertexId()))
5525 {
5526 newSymSets.get(origV.getVertexId()).add(
5527 clonV.getVertexId());
5528 }
5529 else
5530 {
5531 newSymSets.put(origV.getVertexId(),
5532 sgClone.getSymSetForVertexID(
5533 sgClone.getVertexList().get(i)
5534 .getVertexId()));
5535 }
5536 }
5537 else
5538 {
5539 if (newSymSets.containsKey(origV.getVertexId()))
5540 {
5541 newSymSets.get(origV.getVertexId()).add(
5542 clonV.getVertexId());
5543 }
5544 else
5545 {
5546 SymmetricSet ss = new SymmetricSet();
5547 ss.add(clonV.getVertexId());
5548 newSymSets.put(origV.getVertexId(),ss);
5549 }
5550 }
5551 }
5552 // Import all edges from cloned subgraph
5553 for (int i=0; i<sgClone.getEdgeList().size(); i++)
5554 {
5555 addEdge(sgClone.getEdgeList().get(i));
5556 }
5557 // Import all rings from cloned subgraph
5558 for (int i=0; i<sgClone.getRings().size(); i++)
5559 {
5560 addRing(sgClone.getRings().get(i));
5561 }
5562
5563 // project tmp symmetric set into final symmetric sets
5564 Set<SymmetricSet> doneTmpSymSets = new HashSet<SymmetricSet>();
5565 for (Map.Entry<Integer,SymmetricSet> e : newSymSets.entrySet())
5566 {
5567 SymmetricSet tmpSS = e.getValue();
5568 if (doneTmpSymSets.contains(tmpSS))
5569 {
5570 continue;
5571 }
5572 doneTmpSymSets.add(tmpSS);
5573 boolean done = false;
5574 // NB: no need to check all entries of tmpSS: the first is enough
5575 SymmetricSet oldSS;
5576 Iterator<SymmetricSet> iter = getSymSetsIterator();
5577 while (iter.hasNext())
5578 {
5579 oldSS = iter.next();
5580 if (oldSS.contains(tmpSS.getList().get(0)))
5581 {
5582 done = true;
5583 for (Integer symVrtID : tmpSS.getList())
5584 {
5585 // NB this adds only if not already contained
5586 oldSS.add(symVrtID);
5587 }
5588 break;
5589 }
5590 }
5591 if (!done)
5592 {
5593 if (tmpSS.size() <= 1)
5594 {
5595 // tmpSS has always at least one entry: the initial vrtId
5596 continue;
5597 }
5598 //Move tmpSS into a new SS on molGraph
5599 SymmetricSet newSS = new SymmetricSet();
5600 for (Integer symVrtID : tmpSS.getList())
5601 {
5602 newSS.add(symVrtID);
5603 }
5604 addSymmetricSetOfVertices(newSS);
5605 }
5606 }
5607 }

5666 public ArrayList<Integer> findVerticesIds(VertexQuery query, Logger logger)
5667 {
5668 ArrayList<Integer> matches = new ArrayList<>();
5669 for (Vertex v : findVertices(query, logger))
5670 {
5671 matches.add(v.getVertexId());
5672 }
5673 return matches;
