5692
5703 public ArrayList<Vertex> findVertices(VertexQuery vrtxQuery,
5704 boolean purgeSym, Logger logger)
5705 {
5706 ArrayList<Vertex> matches = new ArrayList<>(getVertexList());
5707
5708 logger.log(Level.FINE, "Candidates: " + matches);
5709
5710 //Check condition vertex ID
5711 Integer vidQuery = vrtxQuery.getVertexIDQuery();
5712 if (vidQuery != null)
5713 {
5714 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5715 for (Vertex v : matches)
5716 {
5717 if (v.getVertexId() == vidQuery.intValue())
5718 {
5719 newLst.add(v);
5720 }
5721 }
5722 matches = newLst;
5723 }
5724 logger.log(Level.FINE," After filtering by vertex ID: " + matches);
5725
5726 //Check condition vertex type (NB: essentially the vertex implementation
5727 VertexType vtQuery = vrtxQuery.getVertexTypeQuery();
5728 if (vtQuery != null)
5729 {
5730 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5731 for (Vertex v : matches)
5732 {
5733 if (v.getVertexType() == vtQuery)
5734 {
5735 newLst.add(v);
5736 }
5737 }
5738 matches = newLst;
5739 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After filtering by vertex type: "
5740 + matches);
5741 }
5742
5743 //Check condition building block Type
5744 BBType bbtQuery = vrtxQuery.getVertexBBTypeQuery();
5745 if (bbtQuery != null)
5746 {
5747 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5748 for (Vertex v : matches)
5749 {
5750 if (v.getBuildingBlockType() == bbtQuery)
5751 {
5752 newLst.add(v);
5753 }
5754 }
5755 matches = newLst;
5756 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After filtering by building block "
5757 + "type: " + matches);
5758 }
5759
5760 //Check condition building block ID
5761 Integer bbID = vrtxQuery.getVertexBBIDQuery();
5762 if (bbID != null)
5763 {
5764 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5765 for (Vertex v : matches)
5766 {
5767 if (v.getBuildingBlockId() == bbID.intValue())
5768 {
5769 newLst.add(v);
5770 }
5771 }
5772 matches = newLst;
5773 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After filtering by building block ID: "
5774 + matches);
5775 }
5776
5777 //Check condition: level of vertex
5778 Integer levelQuery = vrtxQuery.getVertexLevelQuery();
5779 if (levelQuery != null)
5780 {
5781 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
5782 for (Vertex v : matches)
5783 {
5784 if (getLevel(v) == levelQuery)
5785 {
5786 newLst.add(v);
5787 }
5788 }
5789 matches = newLst;
5790 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After filtering by level: " + matches);
5791 }
5792
5793 logger.log(Level.FINE, "After all vertex-based filters: " + matches);
5794
5795 List<EdgeQuery> inAndOutEdgeQueries = new ArrayList<>();
5796 inAndOutEdgeQueries.add(vrtxQuery.getInEdgeQuery());
5797 inAndOutEdgeQueries.add(vrtxQuery.getOutEdgeQuery());
5798 for (int i=0; i<2; i++)
5799 {
5800 String inOrOut = "";
5801 if (i==0)
5802 inOrOut = "incoming";
5803 else
5804 inOrOut = "ourgoing";
5805
5806 EdgeQuery edgeQuery = inAndOutEdgeQueries.get(i);
5807 if (edgeQuery == null)
5808 {
5809 continue;
5810 }
5811
5812 EdgeFinder edgeFinder = new EdgeFinder(i-1);
5813
5814 Integer eTrgApIDx = edgeQuery.getTargetAPIdx();
5815 if (eTrgApIDx != null)
5816 {
5817 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5818 for (Vertex v : matches)
5819 {
5820 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5821 {
5822 if (e.getTrgAPID() == eTrgApIDx)
5823 {
5824 newLst.add(v);
5825 break;
5826 }
5827 }
5828 }
5829 matches = newLst;
5830 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After " + inOrOut
5831 + " edge trgAPID filter: " + matches);
5832 }
5833
5834 Integer eInSrcApIDx = edgeQuery.getSourceAPIdx();
5835 if (eInSrcApIDx != null)
5836 {
5837 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5838 for (Vertex v : matches)
5839 {
5840 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5841 {
5842 if (e != null && e.getSrcAPID() == eInSrcApIDx)
5843 {
5844 newLst.add(v);
5845 break;
5846 }
5847 }
5848 }
5849 matches = newLst;
5850 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After " + inOrOut
5851 + " edge srcAPID filter: " + matches);
5852 }
5853
5854 if (i==0)
5855 {
5856 Integer eSrcVrtID = edgeQuery.getSourceVertexId();
5857 if (eSrcVrtID != null)
5858 {
5859 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5860 for (Vertex v : matches)
5861 {
5862 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5863 {
5864 if(e.getSrcAP().getOwner().getVertexId()==eSrcVrtID)
5865 {
5866 newLst.add(v);
5867 break;
5868 }
5869 }
5870 }
5871 matches = newLst;
5872 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After " + inOrOut
5873 + " edge src VertexID filter: " + matches);
5874 }
5875 } else if (i==1) {
5876 Integer eTrgVrtID = edgeQuery.getTargetVertexId();
5877 if (eTrgVrtID != null)
5878 {
5879 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5880 for (Vertex v : matches)
5881 {
5882 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5883 {
5884 if(e.getTrgAP().getOwner().getVertexId()==eTrgVrtID)
5885 {
5886 newLst.add(v);
5887 break;
5888 }
5889 }
5890 }
5891 matches = newLst;
5892 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After " + inOrOut
5893 + " edge trg VertexID filter: " + matches);
5894 }
5895 }
5896
5897 BondType btQuery = edgeQuery.getBondType();
5898 if (btQuery != null)
5899 {
5900 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5901 for (Vertex v : matches)
5902 {
5903 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5904 {
5905 if (e.getBondType() == btQuery)
5906 {
5907 newLst.add(v);
5908 break;
5909 }
5910 }
5911 }
5912 matches = newLst;
5913 logger.log(Level.FINER, " After " + inOrOut
5914 + " edge bond type filter: " + matches);
5915 }
5916
5917 APClass srcAPC = edgeQuery.getSourceAPClass();
5918 if (srcAPC != null)
5919 {
5920 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5921 for (Vertex v : matches)
5922 {
5923 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5924 {
5925 if (e.getSrcAPClass().equals(srcAPC))
5926 {
5927 newLst.add(v);
5928 break;
5929 }
5930 }
5931 }
5932 matches = newLst;
5933 }
5934
5935 APClass trgAPC = edgeQuery.getTargetAPClass();
5936 if (trgAPC != null)
5937 {
5938 ArrayList<Vertex> newLst = new ArrayList<>();
5939 for (Vertex v : matches)
5940 {
5941 for (Edge e : edgeFinder.apply(v))
5942 {
5943 if (e.getTrgAPClass().equals(trgAPC))
5944 {
5945 newLst.add(v);
5946 break;
5947 }
5948 }
5949 }
5950 matches = newLst;
5951 }
5952 logger.log(Level.FINER, "After all " + inOrOut
5953 + " edge-based filters: " + matches);
5954 }
5955
5956 // Identify symmetric sets and keep only one member
5957 if (purgeSym)
5958 removeSymmetryRedundance(matches);
5959
5960 logger.log(Level.FINE, "Final Matches (after symmetry): " + matches);
5961
5962 return matches;
5963 }

5973 private class EdgeFinder implements Function<Vertex,List<Edge>>
5974 {
5975 private int mode = 0;
5976
5981 public EdgeFinder(int i)
5982 {
5983 mode = i;
5984 }
5985
5986 @Override
5987 public List<Edge> apply(Vertex v)
5988 {
5989 List<Edge> edges = new ArrayList<Edge>();
5990 if (mode < 0)
5991 {
5992 Edge eToParent = v.getEdgeToParent();
5993 if (eToParent != null)
5994 edges.add(eToParent);
5995 } else {
5996 for (AttachmentPoint ap : v.getAttachmentPoints())
5997 {
5998 if (!ap.isAvailable() && ap.isSrcInUser())
5999 {
6000 edges.add(ap.getEdgeUser());
6001 }
6002 }
6003 }
6004 return edges;
6005 }
6006 }

6016 public void removeSymmetryRedundance(ArrayList<Vertex> list) {
6017 ArrayList<Vertex> symRedundant = new ArrayList<>();
6018 Iterator<SymmetricSet> itSymm = getSymSetsIterator();
6019 while (itSymm.hasNext())
6020 {
6021 SymmetricSet ss = itSymm.next();
6022 for (Vertex v : list)
6023 {
6024 int vid = v.getVertexId();
6025 if (symRedundant.contains(v))
6026 {
6027 continue;
6028 }
6029 if (ss.contains(vid))
6030 {
6031 for (Integer idVrtInSS : ss.getList())
6032 {
6033 if (idVrtInSS != vid)
6034 {
6035 symRedundant.add(getVertexWithId(idVrtInSS));
6036 }
6037 }
6038 }
6039 }
6040 }
6041 for (Vertex v : symRedundant)
6042 {
6043 list.remove(v);
6044 }
6045 }

6055 public void removeSymmetryRedundantIds(ArrayList<Integer> list) {
6056 ArrayList<Vertex> vList = new ArrayList<>();
6057 for (int vid : list) {
6058 vList.add(getVertexWithId(vid));
6059 }
6060 removeSymmetryRedundance(vList);
6061 list.clear();
6062 for (Vertex v : vList) {
6063 list.add(v.getVertexId());
6064 }

6068
6082 public DGraph editGraph(ArrayList<GraphEdit> edits,
6083 boolean symmetry, FragmentSpace fragSpace, Logger logger)
6084 throws DENOPTIMException
6085 {
6086 DGraph modGraph = this.clone();
6087
6088 for (GraphEdit edit : edits)
6089 {
6090 logger.log(Level.FINE, "Graph edit task: " + edit.getType());
6091
6092 switch (edit.getType())
6093 {
6094 case REPLACECHILD:
6095 {
6096 DGraph inGraph = edit.getIncomingGraph();
6097 VertexQuery query = edit.getVertexQuery();
6098 int idAPOnInGraph = -1; // Initialization to invalid value
6099 Vertex rootOfInGraph = null;
6100 if (edit.getIncomingAPId() != null)
6101 {
6102 AttachmentPoint ap = inGraph.getAPWithId(
6103 edit.getIncomingAPId().intValue());
6104 if (ap == null)
6105 {
6106 String msg = "Skipping " + edit.getType() + " on "
6107 + "graph " + getGraphId() + ". The incoming"
6108 + " graph has no AP with ID = "
6109 + edit.getIncomingAPId() + ". The IDs of "
6110 + "free APs are:";
6111 for (AttachmentPoint freeAP : inGraph.getAvailableAPs())
6112 {
6113 msg = msg + " " + freeAP.getID();
6114 }
6115 msg = msg + ". "
6116 + "Please, use one of those values in "
6117 + "'idAPOnIncomingGraph'.";
6118 logger.log(Level.WARNING, msg);
6119 }
6120 idAPOnInGraph = ap.getIndexInOwner();
6121 rootOfInGraph = ap.getOwner();
6122 } else {
6123 ArrayList<AttachmentPoint> freeAPs =
6124 inGraph.getAvailableAPs();
6125 if (freeAPs.size()==1)
6126 {
6127 AttachmentPoint ap = freeAPs.get(0);
6128 idAPOnInGraph = ap.getIndexInOwner();
6129 rootOfInGraph = ap.getOwner();
6130 } else {
6131 String geClsName = GraphEdit.class.getSimpleName();
6132 String msg = "Skipping " + edit.getType() + " on "
6133 + "graph " + getGraphId() + ". The incoming"
6134 + " graph has more than one free AP ("
6135 + freeAPs.size() + ") and "
6136 + "the " + geClsName + " "
6137 + "does not provide sufficient information "
6138 + "to unambiguously choose one AP. "
6139 + "Please, add 'idAPOnIncomingGraph' in "
6140 + "the definition of " + geClsName + ".";
6141 logger.log(Level.WARNING, msg);
6142 }
6143 }
6144
6145 ArrayList<Vertex> matches = modGraph.findVertices(query,
6146 false, logger);
6147 for (Vertex vertexToReplace : matches)
6148 {
6149 Edge edgeToParent = vertexToReplace.getEdgeToParent();
6150 if (edgeToParent == null)
6151 {
6152 //The matched vertex has no parent, therefore
6153 // the change would correspond to changing the graph
6154 // completely. This is unlikely the desired effect,
6155 // so we do not do anything.
6156 continue;
6157 }
6158 Vertex parent = vertexToReplace.getParent();
6159 int srcApId = edgeToParent.getSrcAPID();
6160
6161 BondType bondType = edgeToParent.getBondType();
6162
6163 modGraph.removeBranchStartingAt(vertexToReplace,symmetry);
6164
6165 modGraph.appendGraphOnGraph(parent, srcApId, inGraph,
6166 rootOfInGraph, idAPOnInGraph, bondType,
6167 new HashMap<Integer,SymmetricSet>(), symmetry);
6168 }
6169 break;
6170 }
6171 case CHANGEVERTEX:
6172 {
6173 // One of the ways to provide the incoming vertex/subgraph
6174 if (edit.getIncomingBBId() > -1
6175 && edit.getIncomingBBType() != null
6176 && edit.getIncomingGraph() == null)
6177 {
6178 ArrayList<Vertex> matches = modGraph.findVertices(
6179 edit.getVertexQuery(), false, logger);
6180 for (Vertex vertexToChange : matches)
6181 {
6182 if (modGraph.containsVertex(vertexToChange))
6183 {
6184 DGraph graph = vertexToChange.getGraphOwner();
6185 graph.replaceVertex(vertexToChange,
6186 edit.getIncomingBBId(),
6187 edit.getIncomingBBType(),
6188 edit.getAPMappig(),
6189 symmetry,
6190 fragSpace);
6191 }
6192 }
6193 }
6194 // Another of the ways to provide the incoming vertex/subgraph
6195 if (edit.getIncomingGraph() != null
6196 && edit.getIncomingBBType() == null)
6197 {
6198 // Since the replaceSingleSubGraph method below does not
6199 // deal with symmetry, we keep symmetrically-redundant
6200 // matches
6201 ArrayList<Vertex> matches = modGraph.findVertices(
6202 edit.getVertexQuery(), false, logger);
6203
6204 for (Vertex vertexToChange : matches)
6205 {
6206 DGraph graph = vertexToChange.getGraphOwner();
6207 DGraph newSubG = edit.getIncomingGraph().clone();
6208 newSubG.renumberGraphVertices();
6209
6210 LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint> apMap =
6211 new LinkedHashMap<AttachmentPoint,AttachmentPoint>();
6212 for (Map.Entry<Integer,Integer> e :
6213 edit.getAPMappig().entrySet())
6214 {
6215 apMap.put(vertexToChange.getAP(e.getKey()),
6216 newSubG.getAvailableAPs().get(
6217 e.getValue()));
6218 }
6219
6220 List<Vertex> oldSubG = new ArrayList<Vertex>();
6221 oldSubG.add(vertexToChange);
6222 graph.replaceSingleSubGraph(oldSubG, newSubG, apMap);
6223 }
6224 }
6225
6226 break;
6227 }
6228 case DELETEVERTEX:
6229 {
6230 ArrayList<Vertex> matches = modGraph.findVertices(
6231 edit.getVertexQuery(), false, logger);
6232 for (Vertex vertexToRemove : matches)
6233 {
6234 if (modGraph.containsVertex(vertexToRemove))
6235 modGraph.removeBranchStartingAt(vertexToRemove,
6236 symmetry);
6237 }
6238 break;
6239 }
6240 }
6241 }
6242 return modGraph;
6243 }

6293 {
6294 //TODO: vertexID uniqueness should be guaranteed by the addVertex method

6303 Set<Integer> unqApIDs = new HashSet<Integer>();

6326 }

6330 {

6402
6403 public static class DENOPTIMGraphDeserializer
6404 implements JsonDeserializer<DGraph>
6405 {
6406 @Override
6407 public DGraph deserialize(JsonElement json, Type typeOfT,
6408 JsonDeserializationContext context) throws JsonParseException
6409 {
6410 JsonObject jsonObject = json.getAsJsonObject();
6411
6412 // First, build a graph with a graph ID and a list of vertices
6413 JsonObject partialJsonObj = new JsonObject();
6414 partialJsonObj.add("graphId", jsonObject.get("graphId"));
6415 partialJsonObj.add("gVertices", jsonObject.get("gVertices"));
6416 // Eventually, also the sym sets will become references... so
6417 // also for symVertices we'll have to go through the list and
6418 // rebuild the references.
6419 partialJsonObj.add("symVertices", jsonObject.get("symVertices"));
6420
6421 Gson gson = new GsonBuilder()
6422 .setExclusionStrategies(new DENOPTIMExclusionStrategyNoAPMap())
6423 .registerTypeAdapter(Vertex.class,
6424 new DENOPTIMVertexDeserializer())
6425 .registerTypeAdapter(APClass.class, new APClassDeserializer())
6426 .setPrettyPrinting()
6427 .create();
6428
6429 DGraph graph = gson.fromJson(partialJsonObj,
6430 DGraph.class);
6431
6432 // Refresh APs
6433 for (Vertex v : graph.getVertexList())
6434 {
6435 // Regenerate reference to fragment owner
6436 v.setGraphOwner(graph);
6437
6438 for (AttachmentPoint ap : v.getAttachmentPoints())
6439 {
6440 // Regenerate reference to AP owner
6441 ap.setOwner(v);
6442 }
6443 }
6444
6445 // Then, recover those members that are heavily based on references:
6446 // edges, rings.
6447 JsonArray edgeArr = jsonObject.get("gEdges").getAsJsonArray();
6448 for (JsonElement e : edgeArr)
6449 {
6450 JsonObject o = e.getAsJsonObject();
6451 AttachmentPoint srcAP = graph.getAPWithId(
6452 o.get("srcAPID").getAsInt());
6453 AttachmentPoint trgAP = graph.getAPWithId(
6454 o.get("trgAPID").getAsInt());
6455
6456 Edge edge = new Edge(srcAP, trgAP,
6457 context.deserialize(o.get("bondType"),BondType.class));
6458 graph.addEdge(edge);
6459 }
6460
6461 // Now, recover the rings
6462 JsonArray ringArr = jsonObject.get("gRings").getAsJsonArray();
6463 for (JsonElement e : ringArr)
6464 {
6465 JsonObject o = e.getAsJsonObject();
6466 Ring ring = new Ring();
6467 for (JsonElement re : o.get("vertices").getAsJsonArray())
6468 {
6469 ring.addVertex(graph.getVertexWithId(re.getAsInt()));
6470 }
6471 ring.setBondType(context.deserialize(o.get("bndTyp"),
6472 BondType.class));
6473 graph.addRing(ring);
6474 }
6475
6476 return graph;
6477 }
6478 }

6481
6489 public static void setScaffold(Vertex v) {
6490 ArrayList<Vertex> newVertexList = new ArrayList<>();
6491
6492 Set<Integer> visited = new HashSet<>();
6493 Queue<Vertex> currLevel = new ArrayDeque<>();
6494 Queue<Vertex> nextLevel = new ArrayDeque<>();
6495 currLevel.add(v);
6496
6497 while (!currLevel.isEmpty()) {
6498 Vertex currVertex = currLevel.poll();
6499
6500 int currId = currVertex.getVertexId();
6501 if (!visited.contains(currId)) {
6502 visited.add(currId);
6503
6504 newVertexList.add(currVertex);
6505
6506 Iterable<Vertex> neighbors = currVertex
6507 .getAttachmentPoints()
6508 .stream()
6509 .map(AttachmentPoint::getEdgeUser)
6510 .filter(e -> e != null)
6511 .map(e -> e.getSrcVertex() == currId ?
6512 e.getTrgAP() : e.getSrcAP())
6513 .map(AttachmentPoint::getOwner)
6514 .collect(Collectors.toList());
6515 for (Vertex adj : neighbors) {
6516 nextLevel.add(adj);
6517 }
6518 }
6519
6520 if (currLevel.isEmpty()) {
6521 currLevel = nextLevel;
6522 nextLevel = new ArrayDeque<>();
6523 }
6524 }
6525
6526 v.getGraphOwner().setVertexList(newVertexList);
6527 }

6711 public static DGraph getEmbeddedGraphInClone(DGraph graphY,

6713 {

6715 return graphY;
6716 Template currentLevelVertex = null;
6717 DGraph currentLevelGraphEmdInB = graphB;
6718 DGraph currentLevelGraphEmbInY = graphY;
6719 for (Template t : path)

6722 .getVertexAtPosition(currentLevelGraphEmdInB.indexOf(t));
6723 currentLevelGraphEmdInB = t.getInnerGraph();
6724 currentLevelGraphEmbInY = currentLevelVertex.getInnerGraph();
6725 }

6739 public List<AttachmentPoint> getInterfaceAPs(List<Vertex> subGraphB)
6740 {
6741 List<AttachmentPoint> interfaceAPs = new ArrayList<AttachmentPoint>();
6742 for (Vertex v : subGraphB)
6743 {
6744 for (AttachmentPoint ap : v.getAttachmentPoints())
6745 {
6746 if (ap.isAvailableThroughout())
6747 continue;
6748 if (ap.isAvailable())
6749 {
6750 // This AP is used across the template boundary
6751 interfaceAPs.add(ap);
6752 } else {
6753 Vertex user = ap.getLinkedAP().getOwner();
6754 if (!subGraphB.contains(user))
6755 {
6756 // AP used to make a connection to outside subgraph
6757 interfaceAPs.add(ap);
6758 }
6759 }
6760 }
6761 }
6762 return interfaceAPs;
